466         std::string tokenizeAndStringify(const char code[], bool simplify = false, bool expand = true, Settings::PlatformType platform = Settings::Native, const char* filename = "test.cpp", bool cpp11 = true) {
467             errout.str("");
468     
469             settings1.debugwarnings = true;
470             settings1.platform(platform);
471             settings1.standards.cpp = cpp11 ? Standards::CPP11 : Standards::CPP03;
472     
473             // tokenize..
474             Tokenizer tokenizer(&settings1, this);
475             std::istringstream istr(code);
476             tokenizer.tokenize(istr, filename);
477             if (simplify)
478                 tokenizer.simplifyTokenList2();
479     
480             // filter out ValueFlow messages..
481             const std::string debugwarnings = errout.str();
482             errout.str("");
483             std::istringstream istr2(debugwarnings.c_str());
484             std::string line;
485             while (std::getline(istr2,line)) {
486                 if (line.find("ValueFlow") == std::string::npos)
487                     errout << line << "\n";
488             }
489     
490             if (tokenizer.tokens())
491                 return tokenizer.tokens()->stringifyList(false, expand, false, true, false, 0, 0);
492             else
493                 return "";
494         }
495     
496         std::string tokenizeAndStringifyWindows(const char code[], bool simplify = false, bool expand = true, Settings::PlatformType platform = Settings::Native, const char* filename = "test.cpp", bool cpp11 = true) {
497             errout.str("");
498     
499             settings_windows.debugwarnings = true;
500             settings_windows.platform(platform);
501             settings_windows.standards.cpp = cpp11 ? Standards::CPP11 : Standards::CPP03;
502     
503             // tokenize..
504             Tokenizer tokenizer(&settings_windows, this);
505             std::istringstream istr(code);
506             tokenizer.tokenize(istr, filename);
507             if (simplify)
508                 tokenizer.simplifyTokenList2();
509     
510             // filter out ValueFlow messages..
511             const std::string debugwarnings = errout.str();
512             errout.str("");
513             std::istringstream istr2(debugwarnings.c_str());
514             std::string line;
515             while (std::getline(istr2,line)) {
516                 if (line.find("ValueFlow") == std::string::npos)
517                     errout << line << "\n";
518             }
519     
520             if (tokenizer.tokens())
521                 return tokenizer.tokens()->stringifyList(false, expand, false, true, false, 0, 0);
522             else
523                 return "";
524         }
525     
526         std::string tokenizeDebugListing(const char code[], bool simplify = false, const char filename[] = "test.cpp") {
527             errout.str("");
528     
529             settings2.standards.c = Standards::C89;
530             settings2.standards.cpp = Standards::CPP03;
531     
532             Tokenizer tokenizer(&settings2, this);
533             std::istringstream istr(code);
534             tokenizer.tokenize(istr, filename);
535     
536             if (simplify)
537                 tokenizer.simplifyTokenList2();
538     
539             // result..
540             return tokenizer.tokens()->stringifyList(true);
541         }

543     
544         void tokenize1() {
545             const char code[] = "void f ( )\n"
546                                 "{ if ( p . y ( ) > yof ) { } }";
547             ASSERT_EQUALS(code, tokenizeAndStringify(code));
548         }
549     
550         void tokenize2() {
551             const char code[] = "{ sizeof a, sizeof b }";
552             ASSERT_EQUALS("{ sizeof ( a ) , sizeof ( b ) }", tokenizeAndStringify(code));
553         }
554     
555         void tokenize3() {
556             const char code[] = "void foo()\n"
557                                 "{\n"
558                                 "    int i;\n"
559                                 "    ABC(for(i=0;i<10;i++) x());\n"
560                                 "}";
561             ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( )\n"
562                           "{\n"
563                           "int i ;\n"
564                           "ABC ( for ( i = 0 ; i < 10 ; i ++ ) x ( ) ) ;\n"
565                           "}", tokenizeAndStringify(code));
566             ASSERT_EQUALS("", errout.str());
567         }

579                           "}", tokenizeAndStringify(code));

584             // Tokenize values

586             ASSERT_EQUALS("; 1E-2 ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; 1E-2 ;"));

588     
589         void tokenize6() {
590             // "&p[1]" => "p+1"
591             /*
592             ASSERT_EQUALS("; x = p + n ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; x = & p [ n ] ;", true));
593             ASSERT_EQUALS("; x = ( p + n ) [ m ] ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; x = & p [ n ] [ m ] ;", true));
594             ASSERT_EQUALS("; x = y & p [ n ] ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; x = y & p [ n ] ;", true));
595             ASSERT_EQUALS("; x = 10 & p [ n ] ;", tokenizeAndStringify(";  x = 10 & p [ n ] ;", true));
596             ASSERT_EQUALS("; x = y [ 10 ] & p [ n ] ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; x = y [ 10 ] & p [ n ] ;", true));
597             ASSERT_EQUALS("; x = ( a + m ) & p [ n ] ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; x = ( a + m ) & p [ n ] ;", true));*/
598             // "*(p+1)" => "p[1]"
599             ASSERT_EQUALS("; x = p [ 1 ] ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; x = * ( p + 1 ) ;", true));
600             ASSERT_EQUALS("; x = p [ 10 ] ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; x = * ( p + 0xA ) ;", true));
601             ASSERT_EQUALS("; x = p [ n ] ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; x = * ( p + n ) ;", true));
602             ASSERT_EQUALS("; x = y * ( p + n ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; x = y * ( p + n ) ;", true));
603             ASSERT_EQUALS("; x = 10 * ( p + n ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; x = 10 * ( p + n ) ;", true));
604             ASSERT_EQUALS("; x = y [ 10 ] * ( p + n ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; x = y [ 10 ] * ( p + n ) ;", true));
605             ASSERT_EQUALS("; x = ( a + m ) * ( p + n ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; x = ( a + m ) * ( p + n ) ;", true));
606     
607             // "*(p-1)" => "p[-1]" and "*(p-n)" => "p[-n]"
608             ASSERT_EQUALS("; x = p [ -1 ] ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; x = *(p - 1);", true));
609             ASSERT_EQUALS("; x = p [ -10 ] ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; x = *(p - 0xA);", true));
610             ASSERT_EQUALS("; x = p [ - n ] ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; x = *(p - n);", true));
611             ASSERT_EQUALS("; x = y * ( p - 1 ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; x = y * (p - 1);", true));
612             ASSERT_EQUALS("; x = 10 * ( p - 1 ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; x = 10 * (p - 1);", true));
613             ASSERT_EQUALS("; x = y [ 10 ] * ( p - 1 ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; x = y[10] * (p - 1);", true));
614             ASSERT_EQUALS("; x = ( a - m ) * ( p - n ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; x = (a - m) * (p - n);", true));
615     
616             // Test that the array-index simplification is not applied when there's no dereference:
617             // "(x-y)" => "(x-y)" and "(x+y)" => "(x+y)"
618             ASSERT_EQUALS("; a = b * ( x - y ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; a = b * (x - y);", true));
619             ASSERT_EQUALS("; a = b * x [ - y ] ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; a = b * *(x - y);", true));
620             ASSERT_EQUALS("; a = a * ( x - y ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; a *= (x - y);", true));
621             ASSERT_EQUALS("; z = a ++ * ( x - y ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; z = a++ * (x - y);", true));
622             ASSERT_EQUALS("; z = a ++ * ( x + y ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; z = a++ * (x + y);", true));
623             ASSERT_EQUALS("; z = a -- * ( x - y ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; z = a-- * (x - y);", true));
624             ASSERT_EQUALS("; z = a -- * ( x + y ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; z = a-- * (x + y);", true));
625             ASSERT_EQUALS("; z = 'a' * ( x - y ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; z = 'a' * (x - y);", true));
626             ASSERT_EQUALS("; z = \"a\" * ( x - y ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; z = \"a\" * (x - y);", true));
627             ASSERT_EQUALS("; z = 'a' * ( x + y ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; z = 'a' * (x + y);", true));
628             ASSERT_EQUALS("; z = \"a\" * ( x + y ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; z = \"a\" * (x + y);", true));
629             ASSERT_EQUALS("; z = foo ( ) * ( x + y ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; z = foo() * (x + y);", true));
630         }

804     
805         void syntax_case_default() { // correct syntax
806             tokenizeAndStringify("void f() {switch (n) { case 0: z(); break;}}");
807             ASSERT_EQUALS("", errout.str());
808     
809             tokenizeAndStringify("void f() {switch (n) { case 0:; break;}}");
810             ASSERT_EQUALS("", errout.str());
811     
812             tokenizeAndStringify("void f() {switch (n) { case 0?1:2 : z(); break;}}");
813             ASSERT_EQUALS("", errout.str());
814     
815             tokenizeAndStringify("void f() {switch (n) { case 0?(1?3:4):2 : z(); break;}}");
816             ASSERT_EQUALS("", errout.str());
817     
818             //allow GCC '({ %name%|%num%|%bool% ; })' statement expression extension
819             tokenizeAndStringify("void f() {switch (n) { case 0?({0;}):1: z(); break;}}");
820             ASSERT_EQUALS("", errout.str());
821     
822             //'b' can be or a macro or an undefined enum
823             tokenizeAndStringify("void f() {switch (n) { case b: z(); break;}}");
824             ASSERT_EQUALS("", errout.str());
825     
826             //valid, when there's this declaration: 'constexpr int g() { return 2; }'
827             tokenizeAndStringify("void f() {switch (n) { case g(): z(); break;}}");
828             ASSERT_EQUALS("", errout.str());
829     
830             //valid, when there's also this declaration: 'constexpr int g[1] = {0};'
831             tokenizeAndStringify("void f() {switch (n) { case g[0]: z(); break;}}");
832             ASSERT_EQUALS("", errout.str());
833     
834             //valid, similar to above case
835             tokenizeAndStringify("void f() {switch (n) { case *g: z(); break;}}");
836             ASSERT_EQUALS("", errout.str());
837     
838             //valid, when 'x' and 'y' are constexpr.
839             tokenizeAndStringify("void f() {switch (n) { case sqrt(x+y): z(); break;}}");
840             ASSERT_EQUALS("", errout.str());
841         }

844             ASSERT_EQUALS("\"test.cpp\"", tokenizeAndStringify("__FILE__"));
845             ASSERT_EQUALS("return -1 ;", tokenizeAndStringify("return - __LINE__;"));
846         }

849             // #3690,#5154
850             const char code[] ="void f() { for each ( char c in MyString ) { Console::Write(c); } }";
851             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { asm ( \"char c in MyString\" ) { Console :: Write ( c ) ; } }" ,tokenizeAndStringify(code));

854         void combineOperators() {
855             ASSERT_EQUALS("; private:", tokenizeAndStringify(";private:", false));
856             ASSERT_EQUALS("; protected:", tokenizeAndStringify(";protected:", false));
857             ASSERT_EQUALS("; public:", tokenizeAndStringify(";public:", false));
858             ASSERT_EQUALS("; __published:", tokenizeAndStringify(";__published:", false));
859             ASSERT_EQUALS("a . public :", tokenizeAndStringify("a.public:", false));
860         }

862         void concatenateNegativeNumber() {
863             ASSERT_EQUALS("i = -12", tokenizeAndStringify("i = -12"));
864             ASSERT_EQUALS("1 - 2", tokenizeAndStringify("1-2"));
865             ASSERT_EQUALS("foo ( -1 ) - 2", tokenizeAndStringify("foo(-1)-2"));
866             ASSERT_EQUALS("int f ( ) { return -2 ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("int f(){return -2;}"));
867             ASSERT_EQUALS("int x [ 2 ] = { -2 , 1 }", tokenizeAndStringify("int x[2] = {-2,1}"));
868     
869             ASSERT_EQUALS("f ( 123 )", tokenizeAndStringify("f(+123)"));
870         }

939         void removeCast13() {
940             // casting deref / address of
941             ASSERT_EQUALS("; int x ; x = * y ;", tokenizeAndStringify(";int x=(int)*y;",true));
942             ASSERT_EQUALS("; int x ; x = & y ;", tokenizeAndStringify(";int x=(int)&y;",true));
943             TODO_ASSERT_EQUALS("; int x ; x = ( INT ) * y ;",
944                                "; int x ; x = * y ;",
945                                tokenizeAndStringify(";int x=(INT)*y;",true)); // INT might be a variable
946             TODO_ASSERT_EQUALS("; int x ; x = ( INT ) & y ;",
947                                "; int x ; x = & y ;",
948                                tokenizeAndStringify(";int x=(INT)&y;",true)); // INT might be a variable
949     
950             // #4899 - False positive on unused variable
951             ASSERT_EQUALS("; float angle ; angle = tilt ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; float angle = (float) tilt;", true)); // status quo
952             ASSERT_EQUALS("; float angle ; angle = ( float ) - tilt ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; float angle = (float) -tilt;", true));
953             ASSERT_EQUALS("; float angle ; angle = ( float ) + tilt ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; float angle = (float) +tilt;", true));
954             ASSERT_EQUALS("; int a ; a = ( int ) ~ c ;", tokenizeAndStringify("; int a = (int)~c;", true));
955         }

978     
979         void inlineasm() {
980             ASSERT_EQUALS("asm ( \"mov ax , bx\" ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("asm { mov ax,bx };"));
981             ASSERT_EQUALS("asm ( \"mov ax , bx\" ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("_asm { mov ax,bx };"));
982             ASSERT_EQUALS("asm ( \"mov ax , bx\" ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("_asm mov ax,bx"));
983             ASSERT_EQUALS("asm ( \"mov ax , bx\" ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("__asm { mov ax,bx };"));
984             ASSERT_EQUALS("asm ( \"\"mov ax,bx\"\" ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("__asm__ __volatile__ ( \"mov ax,bx\" );"));
985             ASSERT_EQUALS("asm ( \"_emit 12h\" ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("__asm _emit 12h ;"));
986             ASSERT_EQUALS("asm ( \"mov a , b\" ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("__asm mov a, b ;"));
987             ASSERT_EQUALS("asm ( \"\"fnstcw %0\" : \"= m\" ( old_cw )\" ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("asm volatile (\"fnstcw %0\" : \"= m\" (old_cw));"));
988             ASSERT_EQUALS("asm ( \"\"fnstcw %0\" : \"= m\" ( old_cw )\" ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify(" __asm__ (\"fnstcw %0\" : \"= m\" (old_cw));"));
989             ASSERT_EQUALS("asm ( \"\"ddd\"\" ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify(" __asm __volatile__ (\"ddd\") ;"));
990             ASSERT_EQUALS("asm ( \"\"ddd\"\" ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify(" __asm __volatile (\"ddd\") ;"));
991             ASSERT_EQUALS("asm ( \"\"mov ax,bx\"\" ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("__asm__ volatile ( \"mov ax,bx\" );"));
992             ASSERT_EQUALS("asm ( \"mov ax , bx\" ) ; int a ;", tokenizeAndStringify("asm { mov ax,bx } int a;"));
993             ASSERT_EQUALS("asm\n\n( \"mov ax , bx __endasm\" ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("__asm\nmov ax,bx\n__endasm;"));
994     
995             // 'asm ( ) ;' should be in the same line
996             ASSERT_EQUALS(";\n\nasm ( \"\"mov ax,bx\"\" ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify(";\n\n__asm__ volatile ( \"mov ax,bx\" );", true));
997         }
998     
999         // #4725 - ^{}
1000         void simplifyAsm2() {
1001             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { asm ( \"^{}\" ) ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { ^{} }"));
1002             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { x ( asm ( \"^{}\" ) ) ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { x(^{}); }"));
1003             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { foo ( A ( ) , asm ( \"^{bar();}\" ) ) ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { foo(A(), ^{ bar(); }); }"));
1004             ASSERT_EQUALS("int f0 ( Args args ) { asm ( \"asm(\"return^{returnsizeof...(Args);}()\")+^{returnsizeof...(args);}()\" )\n"
1005                           "2:\n"
1006                           "|\n"
1007                           "5:\n"
1008                           "6: ;\n"
1009                           "} ;", tokenizeAndStringify("int f0(Args args) {\n"
1010                                   "    return ^{\n"
1011                                   "        return sizeof...(Args);\n"
1012                                   "    }() + ^ {\n"
1013                                   "        return sizeof...(args);\n"
1014                                   "    }();\n"
1015                                   "};"));
1016             ASSERT_EQUALS("int ( ^ block ) ( void ) = asm ( \"^{staticinttest=0;returntest;}\" )\n\n\n;",
1017                           tokenizeAndStringify("int(^block)(void) = ^{\n"
1018                                                "    static int test = 0;\n"
1019                                                "    return test;\n"
1020                                                "};"));
1021     
1022             ASSERT_EQUALS("; return f ( a [ b = c ] , asm ( \"^{}\" ) ) ;",
1023                           tokenizeAndStringify("; return f(a[b=c],^{});")); // #7185
1024             ASSERT_EQUALS("; return f ( asm ( \"^(void){somecode}\" ) ) ;",
1025                           tokenizeAndStringify("; return f(^(void){somecode});"));
1026             ASSERT_EQUALS("; asm ( \"a?(b?(c,asm(\"^{}\")):0):^{}\" ) ;",
1027                           tokenizeAndStringify(";a?(b?(c,^{}):0):^{};"));
1028         }

1040                           "}", tokenizeAndStringify(code, true));

1254         void doWhileAddBraces() {
1255             {
1256                 const char code[] = "do ; while (0);";
1257                 const char result[] = "do { ; } while ( 0 ) ;";
1258     
1259                 ASSERT_EQUALS(result, tokenizeAndStringify(code, false));
1260             }
1261     
1262             {
1263                 const char code[] = "UNKNOWN_MACRO ( do ) ; while ( a -- ) ;";
1264                 const char result[] = "UNKNOWN_MACRO ( do ) ; while ( a -- ) { ; }";
1265     
1266                 ASSERT_EQUALS(result, tokenizeAndStringify(code, true));
1267             }
1268     
1269             {
1270                 const char code[] = "UNKNOWN_MACRO ( do , foo ) ; while ( a -- ) ;";

1272     
1273                 ASSERT_EQUALS(result, tokenizeAndStringify(code, true));
1274             }
1275     
1276             {
1277                 const char code[] = "void foo ( int c , int d ) {\n"
1278                                     " do\n"
1279                                     "  if ( c ) {\n"
1280                                     "   while ( c ) { c -- ; }\n"
1281                                     "  }\n"
1282                                     " while ( -- d > 0 ) ;\n"
1283                                     " return 0 ;\n"
1284                                     "}\n";
1285                 const char result[] =   "void foo ( int c , int d ) {\n"
1286                                         "do {\n"
1287                                         "if ( c ) {\n"
1288                                         "while ( c ) { c -- ; }\n"
1289                                         "} }\n"
1290                                         "while ( -- d > 0 ) ;\n"
1291                                         "return 0 ;\n"
1292                                         "}";
1293                 ASSERT_EQUALS(result, tokenizeAndStringify(code, true));
1294             }
1295     
1296             {
1297                 const char code[] = "void foo ( int c , int d ) {\n"
1298                                     " do\n"
1299                                     "   do c -- ; while ( c ) ;\n"
1300                                     " while ( -- d > 0 ) ;\n"
1301                                     " return 0 ;\n"
1302                                     "}\n";
1303                 const char result[] =   "void foo ( int c , int d ) {\n"
1304                                         "do {\n"
1305                                         "do { c -- ; } while ( c ) ; }\n"
1306                                         "while ( -- d > 0 ) ;\n"
1307                                         "return 0 ;\n"
1308                                         "}";
1309                 ASSERT_EQUALS(result, tokenizeAndStringify(code, true));

1354     
1355         std::string simplifyKnownVariables(const char code[]) {
1356             errout.str("");
1357     
1358             Tokenizer tokenizer(&settings0, this);
1359             std::istringstream istr(code);
1360             tokenizer.tokenize(istr, "test.cpp");
1361     
1362             tokenizer.simplifyKnownVariables();
1363     
1364             return tokenizer.tokens()->stringifyList(0, false);
1365         }

1367         void simplifyKnownVariables1() {
1368             {
1369                 const char code[] = "void f()\n"
1370                                     "{\n"
1371                                     "    int a = 10;\n"
1372                                     "    if (a);\n"
1373                                     "}\n";
1374     
1375                 ASSERT_EQUALS(
1376                     "void f ( ) { int a ; a = 10 ; if ( 10 ) { ; } }",
1377                     simplifyKnownVariables(code));
1378             }
1379     
1380             {
1381                 const char code[] = "void f()\n"
1382                                     "{\n"
1383                                     "    int a = 10;\n"
1384                                     "    if (!a);\n"
1385                                     "}\n";
1386     
1387                 ASSERT_EQUALS(
1388                     "void f ( ) { int a ; a = 10 ; if ( ! 10 ) { ; } }",
1389                     simplifyKnownVariables(code));
1390             }
1391         }

2599         void simplifyKnownVariables52() { // #4728 "= x %op%"
2600             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { int y ; y = 34 + z ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { int x=34; int y=x+z; }", true));
2601             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { int y ; y = 34 - z ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { int x=34; int y=x-z; }", true));
2602             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { int y ; y = 34 * z ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { int x=34; int y=x*z; }", true));
2603             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { int y ; y = 34 / z ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { int x=34; int y=x/z; }", true));
2604             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { int y ; y = 34 % z ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { int x=34; int y=x%z; }", true));
2605             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { int y ; y = 34 & z ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { int x=34; int y=x&z; }", true));
2606             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { int y ; y = 34 | z ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { int x=34; int y=x|z; }", true));
2607             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { int y ; y = 34 ^ z ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { int x=34; int y=x^z; }", true));
2608             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { int y ; y = 34 << z ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { int x=34; int y=x<<z; }", true));
2609             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { int y ; y = 34 >> z ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { int x=34; int y=x>>z; }", true));
2610             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { int y ; y = 34 && z ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { int x=34; int y=x&&z; }", true));
2611             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { int y ; y = 34 || z ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { int x=34; int y=x||z; }", true));
2612             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { int y ; y = 34 > z ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { int x=34; int y=x>z; }", true));
2613             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { int y ; y = 34 >= z ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { int x=34; int y=x>=z; }", true));
2614             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { int y ; y = 34 < z ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { int x=34; int y=x<z; }", true));
2615             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { int y ; y = 34 <= z ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { int x=34; int y=x<=z; }", true));
2616             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { int y ; y = 34 == z ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { int x=34; int y=x==z; }", true));
2617             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { int y ; y = 34 != z ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { int x=34; int y=x!=z; }", true));
2618     
2619             // #4007
2620             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { char *p = 0; int result = p && (!*p); }", true));
2621             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { Foo *p = 0; bool b = (p && (p->type() == 1)); }", true));
2622         }

2822                                     "p = x ;\n"
2823                                     "x = p ;\n"
2824                                     "break ;\n"
2825                                     "case 2 : ;\n"
2826                                     "q = x ;\n"
2827                                     "x = q ;\n"
2828                                     "break ;\n"
2829                                     "}\n"
2830                                     "}";

2867         void simplifyKnownVariablesFunctionCalls() {
2868             {
2869                 const char code[] = "void a(int x);"  // <- x is passed by value
2870                                     "void b() {"
2871                                     "    int x = 123;"
2872                                     "    a(x);"       // <- replace with a(123);
2873                                     "}";
2874                 const char expected[] = "void a ( int x ) ; void b ( ) { a ( 123 ) ; }";
2875                 ASSERT_EQUALS(expected, tokenizeAndStringify(code,true));
2876             }
2877     
2878             {
2879                 const char code[] = "void a(int &x);" // <- x is passed by reference
2880                                     "void b() {"
2881                                     "    int x = 123;"
2882                                     "    a(x);"       // <- don't replace with a(123);
2883                                     "}";
2884                 const char expected[] = "void a ( int & x ) ; void b ( ) { int x ; x = 123 ; a ( x ) ; }";
2885                 ASSERT_EQUALS(expected, tokenizeAndStringify(code,true));
2886             }
2887         }

2930         void file1() {
2931             const char code[] = "a1\n"
2932                                 "#file \"b\"\n"
2933                                 "b1\n"
2934                                 "b2\n"
2935                                 "#endfile\n"
2936                                 "a3\n";
2937     
2938             errout.str("");
2939     
2940             // tokenize..
2941             Tokenizer tokenizer(&settings0, this);
2942             std::istringstream istr(code);
2943             tokenizer.tokenize(istr, "a");
2944     
2945             for (const Token *tok = tokenizer.tokens(); tok; tok = tok->next()) {
2946                 std::ostringstream ostr;
2947                 ostr << char('a' + tok->fileIndex()) << tok->linenr();
2948                 ASSERT_EQUALS(tok->str(), ostr.str());
2949             }
2950         }

3011         void simplifyFunctionParameters() {
3012             {
3013                 const char code[] = "char a [ ABC ( DEF ) ] ;";
3014                 ASSERT_EQUALS(code, tokenizeAndStringify(code));
3015             }
3016     
3017             {
3018                 const char code[] = "module ( a , a , sizeof ( a ) , 0444 ) ;";
3019                 ASSERT_EQUALS("module ( a , a , sizeof ( a ) , 292 ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify(code));
3020             }
3021     
3022             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( int x ) { }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f(x) int x; { }"));
3023             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( int x , char y ) { }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f(x,y) int x; char y; { }"));
3024             ASSERT_EQUALS("int main ( int argc , char * argv [ ] ) { }", tokenizeAndStringify("int main(argc,argv) int argc; char *argv[]; { }"));
3025             ASSERT_EQUALS("int f ( int p , int w , float d ) { }", tokenizeAndStringify("int f(p,w,d) float d; { }"));
3026     
3027             // #1067 - Not simplified. Feel free to fix so it is simplified correctly but this syntax is obsolescent.
3028             ASSERT_EQUALS("int ( * d ( a , b , c ) ) ( ) int a ; int b ; int c ; { }", tokenizeAndStringify("int (*d(a,b,c))()int a,b,c; { }"));
3029     
3030             {
3031                 // This is not a function but the pattern is similar..
3032                 const char code[] = "void foo()"
3033                                     "{"
3034                                     "    if (x)"
3035                                     "        int x;"
3036                                     "    { }"
3037                                     "}";
3038                 ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( ) { if ( x ) { } { } }", tokenizeAndStringify(code, true));
3039             }
3040     
3041             // #3770 - Don't segfault and don't change macro argument as if it's a K&R function argument
3042             {
3043                 const char code[] = "MACRO(a)"
3044                                     ""
3045                                     "void f()"
3046                                     "{"
3047                                     "    SetLanguage();"
3048                                     "    {"
3049                                     "    }"
3050                                     "}";
3051                 ASSERT_EQUALS("MACRO ( a ) void f ( ) { SetLanguage ( ) ; { } }", tokenizeAndStringify(code));
3052             }
3053         }

3250             ASSERT_EQUALS("* x . y = 0 ;", tokenizeAndStringify("*(x.y)=0;", false));
3251         }

3287         void removeParentheses23() { // Ticket #6103
3288             // Reported case
3289             {
3290                 static char code[] = "* * p f ( ) int = { new int ( * [ 2 ] ) ; void }";
3291                 static char  exp[] = "* * p f ( ) int = { new int ( * [ 2 ] ) ; void }";
3292                 ASSERT_EQUALS(exp, tokenizeAndStringify(code));
3293             }
3294             // Various valid cases
3295             {
3296                 static char code[] = "int * f [ 1 ] = { new ( int ) } ;";
3297                 static char  exp[] = "int * f [ 1 ] = { new int } ;";
3298                 ASSERT_EQUALS(exp, tokenizeAndStringify(code));
3299             }
3300             {
3301                 static char code[] = "int * * f [ 1 ] = { new ( int ) [ 1 ] } ;";
3302                 static char  exp[] = "int * * f [ 1 ] = { new int [ 1 ] } ;";
3303                 ASSERT_EQUALS(exp, tokenizeAndStringify(code));
3304             }
3305             {
3306                 static char code[] = "list < int > * f [ 1 ] = { new ( list < int > ) } ;";
3307                 static char  exp[] = "list < int > * f [ 1 ] = { new list < int > } ;";
3308                 ASSERT_EQUALS(exp, tokenizeAndStringify(code));
3309             }
3310             // don't remove parentheses in operator new overload
3311             {
3312                 static char code[] = "void *operator new(__SIZE_TYPE__, int);";
3313                 static char  exp[] = "void * operatornew ( __SIZE_TYPE__ , int ) ;";
3314                 ASSERT_EQUALS(exp, tokenizeAndStringify(code));
3315             }
3316         }

3320             static char  exp[] = "std :: hash < decltype ( t . _data ) > ( ) ( t . _data ) ;";
3321             ASSERT_EQUALS(exp, tokenizeAndStringify(code));

3324         void tokenize_double() {
3325             const char code[] = "void f() {\n"
3326                                 "    double a = 4.2;\n"
3327                                 "    float b = 4.2f;\n"
3328                                 "    double c = 4.2e+10;\n"
3329                                 "    double d = 4.2e-10;\n"
3330                                 "    int e = 4+2;\n"
3331                                 "}";
3332             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) {\n"
3333                           "double a ; a = 4.2 ;\n"
3334                           "float b ; b = 4.2f ;\n"
3335                           "double c ; c = 4.2e+10 ;\n"
3336                           "double d ; d = 4.2e-10 ;\n"
3337                           "int e ; e = 6 ;\n"
3338                           "}", tokenizeAndStringify(code));
3339         }

3444         void simplifyNull() {
3445             {
3446                 const char code[] =
3447                     "int * p = NULL;\n"
3448                     "int * q = __null;\n";
3449                 const char expected[] =
3450                     "int * p ; p = 0 ;\nint * q ; q = 0 ;";
3451                 ASSERT_EQUALS(expected, tokenizeAndStringify(code,true));
3452             }
3453     
3454             ASSERT_EQUALS("( a == nullptr )", tokenizeAndStringify("(a==nullptr)", false, false, Settings::Native, "test.c"));
3455             ASSERT_EQUALS("( a == 0 )", tokenizeAndStringify("(a==nullptr)", false, false, Settings::Native, "test.cpp"));
3456     
3457             ASSERT_EQUALS("if ( p == 0 )", tokenizeAndStringify("if (p==NULL)"));
3458             ASSERT_EQUALS("f ( NULL ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("f(NULL);"));
3459             ASSERT_EQUALS("char * i ; i = 0 ;", tokenizeAndStringify("char* i = (NULL);"));
3460         }

3993         void simplifyKeyword() {
3994             {
3995                 const char code[] = "void f (int a [ static 5] );";
3996                 ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( int a [ 5 ] ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify(code));
3997             }
3998             {
3999                 const char in1[] = "class Base {\n"
4000                                    "  virtual int test() = 0;\n"
4001                                    "};\n"
4002                                    "class Derived : public Base {\n"
4003                                    "  virtual int test() override final {\n"
4004                                    "    for( int Index ( 0 ); Index < 16; ++ Index) { int stub = 0; }\n"
4005                                    "  }\n"
4006                                    "};";
4007                 const char out1[] = "class Base {\n"
4008                                     "virtual int test ( ) = 0 ;\n"
4009                                     "} ;\n"
4010                                     "class Derived : public Base {\n"
4011                                     "virtual int test ( ) {\n"
4012                                     "for ( int Index ( 0 ) ; Index < 16 ; ++ Index ) { int stub ; stub = 0 ; }\n"
4013                                     "}\n"
4014                                     "} ;";
4015                 ASSERT_EQUALS(out1, tokenizeAndStringify(in1));
4016                 const char in2[] =  "class Derived{\n"
4017                                     "  virtual int test() final override;"
4018                                     "};";
4019                 const char out2[] = "class Derived {\n"
4020                                     "virtual int test ( ) override ; } ;";
4021                 ASSERT_EQUALS(out2, tokenizeAndStringify(in2));
4022                 const char in3[] =  "class Derived{\n"
4023                                     "  virtual int test() final override const;"
4024                                     "};";
4025                 const char out3[] = "class Derived {\n"
4026                                     "virtual int test ( ) override const ; } ;";
4027                 ASSERT_EQUALS(out3, tokenizeAndStringify(in3));
4028     
4029                 const char in4 [] = "struct B final : A { void foo(); };";
4030                 const char out4 [] = "struct B : A { void foo ( ) ; } ;";
4031                 ASSERT_EQUALS(out4, tokenizeAndStringify(in4));
4032     
4033                 const char in5 [] = "struct ArrayItemsValidator final {\n"
4034                                     "    SchemaError validate() const override {\n"
4035                                     "        for (; pos < value.size(); ++pos) {\n"
4036                                     "        }\n"
4037                                     "        return none;\n"
4038                                     "    }\n"
4039                                     "};\n";
4040                 const char out5 [] =
4041                     "struct ArrayItemsValidator {\n"
4042                     "SchemaError validate ( ) const override {\n"
4043                     "for ( ; pos < value . size ( ) ; ++ pos ) {\n"
4044                     "}\n"
4045                     "return none ;\n"
4046                     "}\n"
4047                     "} ;";
4048     
4049                 ASSERT_EQUALS(out5, tokenizeAndStringify(in5));
4050             }
4051         }

4087          * tokenize "unsigned i" => "unsigned int i"

4091             // No changes..
4092             {
4093                 const char code[] = "void foo ( unsigned int , float ) ;";
4094                 ASSERT_EQUALS(code, tokenizeAndStringify(code));
4095             }
4096     
4097             // insert "int" after "unsigned"..
4098             {
4099                 const char code1[] = "unsigned i ;";
4100                 const char code2[] = "unsigned int i ;";
4101                 ASSERT_EQUALS(code2, tokenizeAndStringify(code1));
4102             }
4103     
4104             {
4105                 const char code1[] = "int unsigned i ;";
4106                 const char code2[] = "unsigned int i ;";
4107                 ASSERT_EQUALS(code2, tokenizeAndStringify(code1));
4108             }

4111             {
4112                 const char code1[] = "void f() { for (unsigned i=0; i<10; i++) {} }";
4113                 const char code2[] = "void f ( ) { for ( unsigned int i = 0 ; i < 10 ; i ++ ) { } }";
4114                 ASSERT_EQUALS(code2, tokenizeAndStringify(code1));
4115             }

4119                 const char code1[] = "; extern unsigned x;";
4120                 const char code2[] = "; extern unsigned int x ;";
4121                 ASSERT_EQUALS(code2, tokenizeAndStringify(code1));

4302     
4303         void createLinks() {
4304             {
4305                 const char code[] = "class A{\n"
4306                                     " void f() {}\n"
4307                                     "};";
4308                 errout.str("");
4309                 Tokenizer tokenizer(&settings0, this);
4310                 std::istringstream istr(code);
4311                 tokenizer.tokenize(istr, "test.cpp");
4312                 const Token *tok = tokenizer.tokens();
4313                 // A body {}
4314                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, tok->linkAt(2) == tok->tokAt(9));
4315                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, tok->linkAt(9) == tok->tokAt(2));
4316     
4317                 // f body {}
4318                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, tok->linkAt(7) == tok->tokAt(8));
4319                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, tok->linkAt(8) == tok->tokAt(7));
4320     
4321                 // f ()
4322                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, tok->linkAt(5) == tok->tokAt(6));
4323                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, tok->linkAt(6) == tok->tokAt(5));
4324     
4325                 ASSERT_EQUALS("", errout.str());
4326             }
4327     
4328             {
4329                 const char code[] = "void f(){\n"
4330                                     " char a[10];\n"
4331                                     " char *b ; b = new char[a[0]];\n"
4332                                     "};";
4333                 errout.str("");
4334                 Tokenizer tokenizer(&settings0, this);
4335                 std::istringstream istr(code);
4336                 tokenizer.tokenize(istr, "test.cpp");
4337                 const Token *tok = tokenizer.tokens();
4338                 // a[10]
4339                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, tok->linkAt(7) == tok->tokAt(9));
4340                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, tok->linkAt(9) == tok->tokAt(7));
4341     
4342                 // new char[]
4343                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, tok->linkAt(19) == tok->tokAt(24));
4344                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, tok->linkAt(24) == tok->tokAt(19));
4345     
4346                 // a[0]
4347                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, tok->linkAt(21) == tok->tokAt(23));
4348                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, tok->linkAt(23) == tok->tokAt(21));
4349     
4350                 ASSERT_EQUALS("", errout.str());
4351             }
4352     
4353             {
4354                 const char code[] = "void f(){\n"
4355                                     " foo(g());\n"
4356                                     "};";
4357                 errout.str("");
4358                 Tokenizer tokenizer(&settings0, this);
4359                 std::istringstream istr(code);
4360                 tokenizer.tokenize(istr, "test.cpp");
4361                 const Token *tok = tokenizer.tokens();
4362                 // foo(
4363                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, tok->linkAt(6) == tok->tokAt(10));
4364                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, tok->linkAt(10) == tok->tokAt(6));
4365     
4366                 // g(
4367                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, tok->linkAt(8) == tok->tokAt(9));
4368                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, tok->linkAt(9) == tok->tokAt(8));
4369     
4370                 ASSERT_EQUALS("", errout.str());
4371             }
4372     
4373             {
4374                 const char code[] = "bool foo(C<z> a, bar<int, x<float>>& f, int b) {\n"
4375                                     "    return(a<b && b>f);\n"
4376                                     "}";
4377                 errout.str("");
4378                 Tokenizer tokenizer(&settings0, this);
4379                 std::istringstream istr(code);
4380                 tokenizer.tokenize(istr, "test.cpp");
4381                 const Token *tok = tokenizer.tokens();
4382                 // template<
4383                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, tok->tokAt(6) == tok->linkAt(4));
4384                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, tok->tokAt(4) == tok->linkAt(6));
4385     
4386                 // bar<
4387                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, tok->tokAt(17) == tok->linkAt(10));
4388                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, tok->tokAt(10) == tok->linkAt(17));
4389     
4390                 // x<
4391                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, tok->tokAt(16) == tok->linkAt(14));
4392                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, tok->tokAt(14) == tok->linkAt(16));
4393     
4394                 // a<b && b>f
4395                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, 0 == tok->linkAt(28));
4396                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, 0 == tok->linkAt(32));
4397     
4398                 ASSERT_EQUALS("", errout.str());
4399             }

4511             {
4512                 // #6601
4513                 const char code[] = "template<class R> struct FuncType<R(&)()> : FuncType<R()> { };";
4514                 errout.str("");
4515                 Tokenizer tokenizer(&settings0, this);
4516                 std::istringstream istr(code);
4517                 tokenizer.tokenize(istr, "test.cpp");
4518                 const Token *tok = tokenizer.tokens();
4519     
4520                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, tok->linkAt(1) == tok->tokAt(4)); // <class R>
4521                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, tok->linkAt(7) == tok->tokAt(14)); // <R(&)()>
4522                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, tok->linkAt(9) == tok->tokAt(11)); // (&)
4523                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, tok->linkAt(12) == tok->tokAt(13)); // ()
4524                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, tok->linkAt(17) == tok->tokAt(21)); // <R()>
4525                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, tok->linkAt(19) == tok->tokAt(20)); // ()
4526                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, tok->linkAt(22) == tok->tokAt(23)); // {}
4527             }
4528         }
4529     
4530         void simplifyString() {
4531             errout.str("");
4532             Tokenizer tokenizer(&settings0, this);
4533             ASSERT_EQUALS("\"abc\"", tokenizer.simplifyString("\"abc\""));
4534             ASSERT_EQUALS("\"\n\"", tokenizer.simplifyString("\"\\xa\""));
4535             ASSERT_EQUALS("\"3\"", tokenizer.simplifyString("\"\\x33\""));
4536             ASSERT_EQUALS("\"33\"", tokenizer.simplifyString("\"\\x333\""));
4537     
4538             ASSERT_EQUALS("\"a\"", tokenizer.simplifyString("\"\\x61\""));
4539             ASSERT_EQUALS("\"\n1\"", tokenizer.simplifyString("\"\\0121\""));
4540     
4541             ASSERT_EQUALS("\"3\"", tokenizer.simplifyString("\"\\x33\""));
4542             ASSERT_EQUALS("\" 0\"", tokenizer.simplifyString("\"\\0400\""));
4543     
4544             ASSERT_EQUALS("\"\\nhello\"", tokenizer.simplifyString("\"\\nhello\""));
4545     
4546             ASSERT_EQUALS("\"aaa\"", tokenizer.simplifyString("\"\\x61\\x61\\x61\""));
4547             ASSERT_EQUALS("\"\n1\n1\n1\"", tokenizer.simplifyString("\"\\0121\\0121\\0121\""));
4548     
4549             ASSERT_EQUALS("\"\\\\x61\"", tokenizer.simplifyString("\"\\\\x61\""));
4550             ASSERT_EQUALS("\"b\"", tokenizer.simplifyString("\"\\x62\""));
4551             ASSERT_EQUALS("\" 7\"", tokenizer.simplifyString("\"\\0407\""));
4552     
4553             // terminate a string at null character.
4554             ASSERT_EQUALS(std::string("\"a") + '\0' + "\"", tokenizer.simplifyString("\"a\\0\""));
4555         }
4556     
4557         void simplifyConst() {
4558             ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( ) { const int x ; }",
4559                           tokenizeAndStringify("void foo(){ int const x;}"));
4560     
4561             ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( ) { { } const long x ; }",
4562                           tokenizeAndStringify("void foo(){ {} long const x;}"));
4563     
4564             ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( int b , const unsigned int x ) { }",
4565                           tokenizeAndStringify("void foo(int b,unsigned const x){}"));
4566     
4567             ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( ) { bar ( ) ; const char x ; }",
4568                           tokenizeAndStringify("void foo(){ bar(); char const x;}"));
4569     
4570             ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( const char x ) { }",
4571                           tokenizeAndStringify("void foo(char const x){}"));
4572     
4573             ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( int b , const char x ) { }",
4574                           tokenizeAndStringify("void foo(int b,char const x){}"));
4575     
4576             ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( ) { int * const x ; }",
4577                           tokenizeAndStringify("void foo(){ int * const x;}"));
4578     
4579             ASSERT_EQUALS("const int foo ( ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("int const foo ();"));
4580     
4581             ASSERT_EQUALS("const int x ;", tokenizeAndStringify("int const x;"));
4582             ASSERT_EQUALS("const unsigned int x ;", tokenizeAndStringify("unsigned const x;"));
4583             ASSERT_EQUALS("const struct X x ;", tokenizeAndStringify("struct X const x;"));
4584         }
4585     
4586         void switchCase() {
4587             ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( int i ) { switch ( i ) { case -1 : ; break ; } }",
4588                           tokenizeAndStringify("void foo (int i) { switch(i) { case -1: break; } }"));
4589             //ticket #3227
4590             ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( ) { switch ( n ) { label : ; case 1 : ; label1 : ; label2 : ; break ; } }",
4591                           tokenizeAndStringify("void foo(){ switch (n){ label: case 1: label1: label2: break; }}"));
4592         }
4593     
4594         void simplifyPointerToStandardType() {
4595             // Pointer to standard type
4596             ASSERT_EQUALS("char buf [ 100 ] ; readlink ( path , buf , 99 ) ;",
4597                           tokenizeAndStringify("char buf[100] ; readlink(path, &buf[0], 99);",
4598                                                false, true, Settings::Native, "test.c"));
4599     
4600             // Simplification of unknown type - C only
4601             ASSERT_EQUALS("foo data [ 100 ] ; something ( foo ) ;",
4602                           tokenizeAndStringify("foo data[100]; something(&foo[0]);", false, true, Settings::Native, "test.c"));
4603     
4604             // C++: No pointer simplification
4605             ASSERT_EQUALS("foo data [ 100 ] ; something ( & foo [ 0 ] ) ;",
4606                           tokenizeAndStringify("foo data[100]; something(&foo[0]);"));
4607         }

4612             ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned int * f ;", tokenizeAndStringify("unsigned int (*f)();"));
4613             ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned int * * f ;", tokenizeAndStringify("unsigned int * (*f)();"));
4614         }

4687         void removeRedundantAssignment() {
4688             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { int *p, *q; p = q; }", true));
4689             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { int *p = 0, *q; p = q; }", true));
4690             ASSERT_EQUALS("int f ( int * x ) { return * x ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("int f(int *x) { return *x; }", true));
4691         }
4692     
4693         void removedeclspec() {
4694             ASSERT_EQUALS("a b", tokenizeAndStringify("a __declspec ( dllexport ) b"));
4695             ASSERT_EQUALS("a b", tokenizeAndStringify("a _declspec ( dllexport ) b"));
4696             ASSERT_EQUALS("int a ;", tokenizeAndStringify("__declspec(thread) __declspec(align(32)) int a;"));
4697             ASSERT_EQUALS("int i ;", tokenizeAndStringify("__declspec(allocate(\"mycode\")) int i;"));
4698             ASSERT_EQUALS("struct IUnknown ;", tokenizeAndStringify("struct __declspec(uuid(\"00000000-0000-0000-c000-000000000046\")) IUnknown;"));
4699             ASSERT_EQUALS("__property int x [ ] ;", tokenizeAndStringify("__declspec(property(get=GetX, put=PutX)) int x[];"));
4700         }
4701     
4702         void removeattribute() {
4703             ASSERT_EQUALS("short array [ 3 ] ;", tokenizeAndStringify("short array[3] __attribute__ ((aligned));"));
4704             ASSERT_EQUALS("int x [ 2 ] ;", tokenizeAndStringify("int x[2] __attribute__ ((packed));"));
4705             ASSERT_EQUALS("int vecint ;", tokenizeAndStringify("int __attribute__((mode(SI))) __attribute__((vector_size (16))) vecint;"));
4706     
4707             // alternate spelling #5328
4708             ASSERT_EQUALS("short array [ 3 ] ;", tokenizeAndStringify("short array[3] __attribute ((aligned));"));
4709             ASSERT_EQUALS("int x [ 2 ] ;", tokenizeAndStringify("int x[2] __attribute ((packed));"));
4710             ASSERT_EQUALS("int vecint ;", tokenizeAndStringify("int __attribute((mode(SI))) __attribute((vector_size (16))) vecint;"));
4711         }

4713         void functionAttributeBefore() {
4714             const char code[] = "void __attribute__((pure)) __attribute__((nothrow)) __attribute__((const)) func1();\n"
4715                                 "void __attribute__((__pure__)) __attribute__((__nothrow__)) __attribute__((__const__)) func2();\n"
4716                                 "void __attribute__((nothrow)) __attribute__((pure)) __attribute__((const)) func3();\n"
4717                                 "void __attribute__((__nothrow__)) __attribute__((__pure__)) __attribute__((__const__)) func4();\n"
4718                                 "void __attribute__((noreturn)) func5();";
4719             const char expected[] = "void func1 ( ) ; void func2 ( ) ; void func3 ( ) ; void func4 ( ) ; void func5 ( ) ;";
4720     
4721             errout.str("");
4722     
4723             // tokenize..
4724             Tokenizer tokenizer(&settings0, this);
4725             std::istringstream istr(code);
4726             tokenizer.tokenize(istr, "test.cpp");
4727     
4728             // Expected result..
4729             ASSERT_EQUALS(expected, tokenizer.tokens()->stringifyList(0, false));
4730     
4731             const Token * func1 = Token::findsimplematch(tokenizer.tokens(), "func1");
4732             const Token * func2 = Token::findsimplematch(tokenizer.tokens(), "func2");
4733             const Token * func3 = Token::findsimplematch(tokenizer.tokens(), "func3");
4734             const Token * func4 = Token::findsimplematch(tokenizer.tokens(), "func4");
4735             const Token * func5 = Token::findsimplematch(tokenizer.tokens(), "func5");
4736     
4737             ASSERT(func1 && func1->isAttributePure() && func1->isAttributeNothrow() && func1->isAttributeConst());
4738             ASSERT(func2 && func2->isAttributePure() && func2->isAttributeNothrow() && func2->isAttributeConst());
4739             ASSERT(func3 && func3->isAttributePure() && func3->isAttributeNothrow() && func3->isAttributeConst());
4740             ASSERT(func4 && func4->isAttributePure() && func4->isAttributeNothrow() && func4->isAttributeConst());
4741             ASSERT(func5 && func5->isAttributeNoreturn());
4742         }

4775         void cpp03template1() {
4776             {
4777                 const char *code = "template<typename> struct extent {};";
4778                 ASSERT_EQUALS("template < typename > struct extent { } ;", tokenizeAndStringify(code));
4779             }
4780             {
4781                 const char *code = "template<typename> struct extent;";
4782                 ASSERT_EQUALS("template < typename > struct extent ;", tokenizeAndStringify(code));
4783             }
4784             {
4785                 const char *code = "template<typename, unsigned = 0> struct extent;";
4786                 ASSERT_EQUALS("template < typename , unsigned int = 0 > struct extent ;", tokenizeAndStringify(code));
4787             }
4788         }

4823                                  "template <class T> class Disposer; "
4824                                  "template <typename T, class D = Disposer<T>> class Shim {}; "
4825                                  "class B : public Shim<A> {};");
4826             tokenizeAndStringify("template <class ELFT> class ELFObjectImage {}; "
4827                                  "ObjectImage *createObjectImage() { "
4828                                  "  return new ELFObjectImage<ELFType<little>>(Obj); "
4829                                  "} "
4830                                  "void resolveX86_64Relocation() { "
4831                                  "  reinterpret_cast<int>(0); "
4832                                  "}");
4833             tokenizeAndStringify("template<typename value_type, typename function_type> "
4834                                  "value_type Base(const value_type x, const value_type dx, function_type func, int type_deriv) { "
4835                                  "   return 0.0; "
4836                                  "}; "
4837                                  "namespace { "
4838                                  "  template<class DC> class C { "
4839                                  "    void Fun(int G, const double x); "
4840                                  "  }; "
4841                                  "  template<class DC> void C<DC>::Fun(int G, const double x) {"
4842                                  "    Base<double, CDFFunctor<DC>>(2, 2, f, 0); "
4843                                  "  }; "
4844                                  "  template<class DC> class C2 {}; "
4845                                  "}");
4846         }

4848         void cpp14template() { // Ticket #6708
4849             tokenizeAndStringify("template <typename T> "
4850                                  "decltype(auto) forward(T& t) { return 0; }");
4851         }
4852     
4853         void arraySize() {
4854             ASSERT_EQUALS("; int a [ 3 ] = { 1 , 2 , 3 } ;", tokenizeAndStringify(";int a[]={1,2,3};"));
4855             ASSERT_EQUALS("; int a [ 3 ] = { 1 , 2 , 3 } ;", tokenizeAndStringify(";int a[]={1,2,3,};"));
4856             ASSERT_EQUALS("; foo a [ 3 ] = { { 1 , 2 } , { 3 , 4 } , { 5 , 6 } } ;", tokenizeAndStringify(";foo a[]={{1,2},{3,4},{5,6}};"));
4857             ASSERT_EQUALS("; int a [ 1 ] = { foo < bar1 , bar2 > ( 123 , 4 ) } ;", tokenizeAndStringify(";int a[]={foo<bar1,bar2>(123,4)};"));
4858             ASSERT_EQUALS("; int a [ 2 ] = { b > c ? 1 : 2 , 3 } ;", tokenizeAndStringify(";int a[]={ b>c?1:2,3};"));
4859             ASSERT_EQUALS("int main ( ) { int a [ 2 ] = { b < c ? 1 : 2 , 3 } }", tokenizeAndStringify("int main(){int a[]={b<c?1:2,3}}"));
4860             ASSERT_EQUALS("; int a [ 3 ] = { ABC , 2 , 3 } ;", tokenizeAndStringify(";int a[]={ABC,2,3};"));
4861             ASSERT_EQUALS("; int a [ 3 ] = { [ 2 ] = 5 } ;", tokenizeAndStringify(";int a[]={ [2] = 5 };"));
4862             ASSERT_EQUALS("; int a [ 5 ] = { 1 , 2 , [ 2 ] = 5 , 3 , 4 } ;", tokenizeAndStringify(";int a[]={ 1, 2, [2] = 5, 3, 4 };"));
4863             ASSERT_EQUALS("; int a [ ] = { 1 , 2 , [ x ] = 5 , 3 , 4 } ;", tokenizeAndStringify(";int a[]={ 1, 2, [x] = 5, 3, 4 };"));
4864         }
4865     
4866         void labels() {
4867             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { ab : ; a = 0 ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { ab: a=0; }"));
4868             //ticket #3176
4869             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { ab : ; ( * func ) ( ) ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { ab: (*func)(); }"));
4870             //with '*' operator
4871             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { ab : ; * b = 0 ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { ab: *b=0; }"));
4872             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { ab : ; * * b = 0 ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { ab: **b=0; }"));
4873             //with '&' operator
4874             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { ab : ; & b = 0 ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { ab: &b=0; }"));
4875             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { ab : ; & ( b . x ) = 0 ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { ab: &(b->x)=0; }"));
4876             //with '(' parentheses
4877             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { ab : ; * ( * b ) . x = 0 ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { ab: *(* b)->x=0; }"));
4878             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { ab : ; ( * * b ) . x = 0 ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { ab: (** b).x=0; }"));
4879             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { ab : ; & ( * b . x ) = 0 ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { ab: &(*b.x)=0; }"));
4880             //with '{' parentheses
4881             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { ab : ; { b = 0 ; } }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { ab: {b=0;} }"));
4882             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { ab : ; { * b = 0 ; } }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { ab: { *b=0;} }"));
4883             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { ab : ; { & b = 0 ; } }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { ab: { &b=0;} }"));
4884             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { ab : ; { & ( * b . x ) = 0 ; } }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { ab: {&(*b.x)=0;} }"));
4885             //with unhandled MACRO() code
4886             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { MACRO ( ab : b = 0 ; , foo ) }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { MACRO(ab: b=0;, foo)}"));
4887             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { MACRO ( bar , ab : { & ( * b . x ) = 0 ; } ) }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { MACRO(bar, ab: {&(*b.x)=0;})}"));
4888         }

5365         void simplifyNamespaceStd() {
5366             static const char code1[] = "map<foo, bar> m;"; // namespace std is not used
5367             ASSERT_EQUALS("map < foo , bar > m ;", tokenizeAndStringify(code1, false));
5368     
5369             static const char code2[] = "using namespace std;\n"
5370                                         "map<foo, bar> m;";
5371             ASSERT_EQUALS("std :: map < foo , bar > m ;", tokenizeAndStringify(code2, false));
5372     
5373             static const char code3[] = "using namespace std;\n"
5374                                         "string s;";
5375             ASSERT_EQUALS("std :: string s ;", tokenizeAndStringify(code3, false));
5376     
5377             static const char code4[] = "using namespace std;\n"
5378                                         "void foo() {swap(a, b); }";
5379             ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( ) { std :: swap ( a , b ) ; }", tokenizeAndStringify(code4, false));
5380     
5381             static const char code5[] = "using namespace std;\n"
5382                                         "void foo() {map(a, b); }"; // Thats obviously not std::map<>
5383             ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( ) { map ( a , b ) ; }", tokenizeAndStringify(code5, false));
5384     
5385             static const char code6[] = "using namespace std;\n"
5386                                         "string<wchar_t> s;"; // Thats obviously not std::string
5387             ASSERT_EQUALS("string < wchar_t > s ;", tokenizeAndStringify(code6, false));
5388     
5389             static const char code7[] = "using namespace std;\n"
5390                                         "swap s;"; // Thats obviously not std::swap
5391             ASSERT_EQUALS("swap s ;", tokenizeAndStringify(code7, false));
5392     
5393             static const char code8[] = "using namespace std;\n"
5394                                         "std::string s;";
5395             ASSERT_EQUALS("std :: string s ;", tokenizeAndStringify(code8, false));
5396     
5397             static const char code9[] = "using namespace std;\n"
5398                                         "tr1::function <void(int)> f;";
5399             ASSERT_EQUALS("tr1 :: function < void ( int ) > f ;", tokenizeAndStringify(code9, false, true, Settings::Native, "test.cpp", false));
5400             ASSERT_EQUALS("std :: function < void ( int ) > f ;", tokenizeAndStringify(code9, false, true, Settings::Native, "test.cpp", true));
5401     
5402             static const char code10[] = "std::tr1::function <void(int)> f;";
5403             ASSERT_EQUALS("std :: tr1 :: function < void ( int ) > f ;", tokenizeAndStringify(code10, false, true, Settings::Native, "test.cpp", false));
5404             ASSERT_EQUALS("std :: function < void ( int ) > f ;", tokenizeAndStringify(code10, false, true, Settings::Native, "test.cpp", true));
5405     
5406             // #4042 (Do not add 'std ::' to variables)
5407             static const char code11[] = "using namespace std;\n"
5408                                          "const char * string = \"Hi\";";
5409             ASSERT_EQUALS("const char * string ; string = \"Hi\" ;", tokenizeAndStringify(code11, false));
5410     
5411             static const char code12[] = "using namespace std;\n"
5412                                          "string f(const char * string) {\n"
5413                                          "    cout << string << endl;\n"
5414                                          "    return string;\n"
5415                                          "}";
5416             static const char expected12[] = "std :: string f ( const char * string ) {\n"
5417                                              "std :: cout << string << std :: endl ;\n"
5418                                              "return string ;\n"
5419                                              "}";
5420             ASSERT_EQUALS(expected12, tokenizeAndStringify(code12, false));
5421     
5422             static const char code13[] = "using namespace std;\n"
5423                                          "try { }\n"
5424                                          "catch(std::exception &exception) { }";
5425             static const char expected13[] = "try { }\n"
5426                                              "catch ( std :: exception & exception ) { }";
5427             ASSERT_EQUALS(expected13, tokenizeAndStringify(code13, false));
5428     
5429             // #5773 (Don't prepend 'std ::' to function definitions)
5430             static const char code14[] = "using namespace std;\n"
5431                                          "class C {\n"
5432                                          "    void search() {}\n"
5433                                          "    void search() const {}\n"
5434                                          "    void search() THROW_MACRO {}\n"
5435                                          "};";
5436             static const char expected14[] = "class C {\n"
5437                                              "void search ( ) { }\n"
5438                                              "void search ( ) const { }\n"
5439                                              "void search ( ) { }\n"
5440                                              "} ;";
5441             ASSERT_EQUALS(expected14, tokenizeAndStringify(code14, false));
5442         }

5444         void microsoftMemory() {
5445             const char code1a[] = "void foo() { int a[10], b[10]; CopyMemory(a, b, sizeof(a)); }";
5446             ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( ) { int a [ 10 ] ; int b [ 10 ] ; memcpy ( a , b , sizeof ( a ) ) ; }", tokenizeAndStringify(code1a,false,true,Settings::Win32A));
5447     
5448             const char code1b[] = "void foo() { int a[10], b[10]; RtlCopyMemory(a, b, sizeof(a)); }";
5449             ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( ) { int a [ 10 ] ; int b [ 10 ] ; memcpy ( a , b , sizeof ( a ) ) ; }", tokenizeAndStringify(code1b,false,true,Settings::Win32A));
5450     
5451             const char code1c[] = "void foo() { int a[10], b[10]; RtlCopyBytes(a, b, sizeof(a)); }";
5452             ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( ) { int a [ 10 ] ; int b [ 10 ] ; memcpy ( a , b , sizeof ( a ) ) ; }", tokenizeAndStringify(code1c,false,true,Settings::Win32A));
5453     
5454             const char code2a[] = "void foo() { int a[10]; FillMemory(a, sizeof(a), 255); }";
5455             ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( ) { int a [ 10 ] ; memset ( a , 255 , sizeof ( a ) ) ; }", tokenizeAndStringify(code2a,false,true,Settings::Win32A));
5456             const char code2b[] = "void foo() { int a[10]; RtlFillMemory(a, sizeof(a), 255); }";
5457             ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( ) { int a [ 10 ] ; memset ( a , 255 , sizeof ( a ) ) ; }", tokenizeAndStringify(code2b,false,true,Settings::Win32A));
5458             const char code2c[] = "void foo() { int a[10]; RtlFillBytes(a, sizeof(a), 255); }";
5459             ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( ) { int a [ 10 ] ; memset ( a , 255 , sizeof ( a ) ) ; }", tokenizeAndStringify(code2c,false,true,Settings::Win32A));
5460     
5461             const char code3a[] = "void foo() { int a[10], b[10]; MoveMemory(a, b, sizeof(a)); }";
5462             ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( ) { int a [ 10 ] ; int b [ 10 ] ; memmove ( a , b , sizeof ( a ) ) ; }", tokenizeAndStringify(code3a,false,true,Settings::Win32A));
5463             const char code3b[] = "void foo() { int a[10], b[10]; RtlMoveMemory(a, b, sizeof(a)); }";
5464             ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( ) { int a [ 10 ] ; int b [ 10 ] ; memmove ( a , b , sizeof ( a ) ) ; }", tokenizeAndStringify(code3b,false,true,Settings::Win32A));
5465     
5466             const char code4a[] = "void foo() { int a[10]; ZeroMemory(a, sizeof(a)); }";
5467             ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( ) { int a [ 10 ] ; memset ( a , 0 , sizeof ( a ) ) ; }", tokenizeAndStringify(code4a,false,true,Settings::Win32A));
5468             const char code4b[] = "void foo() { int a[10]; RtlZeroMemory(a, sizeof(a)); }";
5469             ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( ) { int a [ 10 ] ; memset ( a , 0 , sizeof ( a ) ) ; }", tokenizeAndStringify(code4b,false,true,Settings::Win32A));
5470             const char code4c[] = "void foo() { int a[10]; RtlZeroBytes(a, sizeof(a)); }";
5471             ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( ) { int a [ 10 ] ; memset ( a , 0 , sizeof ( a ) ) ; }", tokenizeAndStringify(code4c,false,true,Settings::Win32A));
5472             const char code4d[] = "void foo() { int a[10]; RtlSecureZeroMemory(a, sizeof(a)); }";
5473             ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( ) { int a [ 10 ] ; memset ( a , 0 , sizeof ( a ) ) ; }", tokenizeAndStringify(code4d,false,true,Settings::Win32A));
5474     
5475             const char code5[] = "void foo() { int a[10], b[10]; RtlCompareMemory(a, b, sizeof(a)); }";
5476             ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( ) { int a [ 10 ] ; int b [ 10 ] ; memcmp ( a , b , sizeof ( a ) ) ; }", tokenizeAndStringify(code5,false,true,Settings::Win32A));
5477     
5478             const char code6[] = "void foo() { ZeroMemory(f(1, g(a, b)), h(i, j(0, 1))); }";
5479             ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( ) { memset ( f ( 1 , g ( a , b ) ) , 0 , h ( i , j ( 0 , 1 ) ) ) ; }", tokenizeAndStringify(code6,false,true,Settings::Win32A));
5480     
5481             const char code7[] = "void foo() { FillMemory(f(1, g(a, b)), h(i, j(0, 1)), 255); }";
5482             ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( ) { memset ( f ( 1 , g ( a , b ) ) , 255 , h ( i , j ( 0 , 1 ) ) ) ; }", tokenizeAndStringify(code7,false,true,Settings::Win32A));
5483         }

5601         void simplifySQL() {
5602             // Oracle PRO*C extensions for inline SQL. Just replace the SQL with "asm()" to fix wrong error messages
5603             // ticket: #1959
5604             ASSERT_EQUALS("asm ( \"\"EXEC SQL SELECT A FROM B\"\" ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("EXEC SQL SELECT A FROM B;",false));
5605             ASSERT_EQUALS("asm ( \"\"EXEC SQL\"\" ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("EXEC SQL",false));
5606     
5607         }
5608     
5609         void simplifyCAlternativeTokens() {
5610             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { if ( a && b ) { ; } }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { if (a and b); }"));
5611             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { if ( a || b ) { ; } }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { if (a or b); }"));
5612             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { if ( a & b ) { ; } }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { if (a bitand b); }"));
5613             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { if ( a | b ) { ; } }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { if (a bitor b); }"));
5614             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { if ( a ^ b ) { ; } }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { if (a xor b); }"));
5615             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { if ( ~ b ) { ; } }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { if (compl b); }"));
5616             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { if ( ! b ) { ; } }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { if (not b); }"));
5617             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { if ( a != b ) { ; } }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { if (a not_eq b); }"));
5618             // #6201
5619             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { if ( ! c || ! memcmp ( a , b , s ) ) { ; } }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { if (!c or !memcmp(a, b, s)); }"));
5620     
5621             ASSERT_EQUALS("\n" // #6029
5622                           "\n"
5623                           "##file 0\n"
5624                           "1: void f ( bool b@1 ) { if ( ! b@1 ) { ; } }\n",
5625                           tokenizeDebugListing("void f(bool b) { if (not b); }"));
5626         }
5627     
5628         void simplifyCalculations() {
5629             ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( char str [ ] ) { char x ; x = * str ; }",
5630                           tokenizeAndStringify("void foo ( char str [ ] ) { char x = 0 | ( * str ) ; }", true));
5631             ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( ) { if ( b ) { } }",
5632                           tokenizeAndStringify("void foo ( ) { if (b | 0) { } }", true));
5633             ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( ) { if ( b ) { } }",
5634                           tokenizeAndStringify("void foo ( ) { if (0 | b) { } }", true));
5635             ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( int b ) { int a ; a = b ; bar ( a ) ; }",
5636                           tokenizeAndStringify("void foo ( int b ) { int a = b | 0 ; bar ( a ) ; }", true));
5637             ASSERT_EQUALS("void foo ( int b ) { int a ; a = b ; bar ( a ) ; }",
5638                           tokenizeAndStringify("void foo ( int b ) { int a = 0 | b ; bar ( a ) ; }", true));
5639     
5640             // ticket #3093
5641             ASSERT_EQUALS("int f ( ) { return 15 ; }",
5642                           tokenizeAndStringify("int f() { int a = 10; int b = 5; return a + b; }", true));
5643             ASSERT_EQUALS("int f ( ) { return a ; }",
5644                           tokenizeAndStringify("int f() { return a * 1; }", true));
5645             ASSERT_EQUALS("int f ( int a ) { return 0 ; }",
5646                           tokenizeAndStringify("int f(int a) { return 0 * a; }", true));
5647             ASSERT_EQUALS("bool f ( int i ) { switch ( i ) { case 15 : ; return true ; } }",
5648                           tokenizeAndStringify("bool f(int i) { switch (i) { case 10 + 5: return true; } }", true));
5649     
5650             // ticket #3576 - False positives in boolean expressions
5651             ASSERT_EQUALS("int foo ( ) { return 1 ; }",
5652                           tokenizeAndStringify("int foo ( ) { int i; int j; i = 1 || j; return i; }", true));
5653     
5654             ASSERT_EQUALS("int foo ( ) { return 0 ; }",
5655                           tokenizeAndStringify("int foo ( ) { int i; int j; i = 0 && j; return i; }", true));        // ticket #3576 - False positives in boolean expressions
5656     
5657             // ticket #3723 - Simplify condition (0 && a < 123)
5658             ASSERT_EQUALS("( 0 )",
5659                           tokenizeAndStringify("( 0 && a < 123 )", true));
5660     
5661             // ticket #3964 - simplify numeric calculations in tokenization
5662             ASSERT_EQUALS("char a [ 10 ] ;", tokenizeAndStringify("char a[9+1];"));
5663     
5664             // ticket #4931
5665             ASSERT_EQUALS("dostuff ( 1 ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("dostuff(9&&8);", true));
5666         }
5667     
5668         void simplifyRoundCurlyParentheses() {
5669             ASSERT_EQUALS("; x = 123 ;", tokenizeAndStringify(";x=({123;});"));
5670             ASSERT_EQUALS("; x = y ;", tokenizeAndStringify(";x=({y;});"));
5671         }

5706         void simplifyOperatorName3() {
5707             // #2615
5708             const char code[] = "void f() {"
5709                                 "static_cast<ScToken*>(xResult.operator->())->GetMatrix();"
5710                                 "}";
5711             const char result[] = "void f ( ) { static_cast < ScToken * > ( xResult . operator. ( ) ) . GetMatrix ( ) ; }";
5712             ASSERT_EQUALS(result, tokenizeAndStringify(code,false));
5713         }

5727             const char result2[] = "std :: ostream & operator<< ( std :: ostream & s , const Fred & f ) ;";
5728             ASSERT_EQUALS(result2, tokenizeAndStringify(code2,false));
5729         }

5747         void simplifyOperatorName8() { // ticket #5706
5748             const char code1[] = "value_type * operator += (int) noexcept ;";
5749             const char result1[] = "value_type * operator+= ( int ) noexcept ;";
5750             ASSERT_EQUALS(result1, tokenizeAndStringify(code1,false));
5751     
5752             const char code2[] = "value_type * operator += (int) noexcept ( true ) ;";
5753             const char result2[] = "value_type * operator+= ( int ) noexcept ( true ) ;";
5754             ASSERT_EQUALS(result2, tokenizeAndStringify(code2,false));
5755     
5756             const char code3[] = "value_type * operator += (int) throw ( ) ;";
5757             const char result3[] = "value_type * operator+= ( int ) throw ( ) ;";
5758             ASSERT_EQUALS(result3, tokenizeAndStringify(code3,false));
5759     
5760             const char code4[] = "value_type * operator += (int) const noexcept ;";
5761             const char result4[] = "value_type * operator+= ( int ) const noexcept ;";
5762             ASSERT_EQUALS(result4, tokenizeAndStringify(code4,false));
5763     
5764             const char code5[] = "value_type * operator += (int) const noexcept ( true ) ;";
5765             const char result5[] = "value_type * operator+= ( int ) const noexcept ( true ) ;";
5766             ASSERT_EQUALS(result5, tokenizeAndStringify(code5,false));
5767     
5768             const char code6[] = "value_type * operator += (int) const throw ( ) ;";
5769             const char result6[] = "value_type * operator+= ( int ) const throw ( ) ;";
5770             ASSERT_EQUALS(result6, tokenizeAndStringify(code6,false));
5771         }

5777     
5778         void simplifyNullArray() {
5779             ASSERT_EQUALS("* ( foo . bar [ 5 ] ) = x ;", tokenizeAndStringify("0[foo.bar[5]] = x;"));
5780         }
5781     
5782         void removeMacrosInGlobalScope() {
5783             // remove some unhandled macros in the global scope.
5784             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() NOTHROW { }"));
5785             ASSERT_EQUALS("struct Foo { } ;", tokenizeAndStringify("struct __declspec(dllexport) Foo {};"));
5786             ASSERT_EQUALS("namespace { }", tokenizeAndStringify("ABA() namespace { }"));
5787     
5788             // #3750
5789             ASSERT_EQUALS("; foo :: foo ( ) { }",
5790                           tokenizeAndStringify("; AB(foo*) foo::foo() { }"));
5791     
5792             // #4834
5793             ASSERT_EQUALS("A(B) foo ( ) { }", tokenizeAndStringify("A(B) foo() {}"));
5794     
5795             // #3855
5796             ASSERT_EQUALS("; class foo { }",
5797                           tokenizeAndStringify("; AB class foo { }"));
5798             ASSERT_EQUALS("; CONST struct ABC abc ;",
5799                           tokenizeAndStringify("; CONST struct ABC abc ;"));
5800         }
5801     
5802         void removeMacroInVarDecl() { // #4304
5803             // only remove macros with parentheses (those hurt most)
5804             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { PROGMEM int x ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { PROGMEM int x ; }"));
5805             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { int x ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { SECTION(\".data.ro\") int x ; }"));
5806     
5807             // various variable declarations
5808             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { CONST int x ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { SECTION(\".data.ro\") CONST int x ; }"));
5809             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { char a [ 4 ] ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { SECTION(\".data.ro\") char a[4]; }"));
5810             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { const char a [ 4 ] ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { SECTION(\".data.ro\") const char a[4]; }"));
5811             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { struct ABC abc ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { SECTION(\".data.ro\") struct ABC abc; }"));
5812             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { CONST struct ABC abc ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { SECTION(\".data.ro\") CONST struct ABC abc; }"));
5813         }
5814     
5815         void multipleAssignment() {
5816             ASSERT_EQUALS("a = b = 0 ;", tokenizeAndStringify("a=b=0;"));
5817         }

6310     
6311             const char code2[] = "LPCVOID a; ::LPCVOID b; foo::LPCVOID c;";
