6313             ASSERT_EQUALS(expected2, tokenizeAndStringifyWindows(code2, true, true, Settings::Win32A));
6314         }
6315     
6316         void isZeroNumber() const {
6317             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, Tokenizer::isZeroNumber("0.0"));
6318             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, Tokenizer::isZeroNumber("+0.0"));
6319             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, Tokenizer::isZeroNumber("-0.0"));
6320             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, Tokenizer::isZeroNumber("+0L"));
6321             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, Tokenizer::isZeroNumber("+0"));
6322             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, Tokenizer::isZeroNumber("-0"));
6323             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, Tokenizer::isZeroNumber("-0E+0"));
6324     
6325             ASSERT_EQUALS(false, Tokenizer::isZeroNumber("1.0"));
6326             ASSERT_EQUALS(false, Tokenizer::isZeroNumber("+1.0"));
6327             ASSERT_EQUALS(false, Tokenizer::isZeroNumber("-1"));
6328             ASSERT_EQUALS(false, Tokenizer::isZeroNumber(""));
6329             ASSERT_EQUALS(false, Tokenizer::isZeroNumber("garbage"));
6330             ASSERT_EQUALS(false, Tokenizer::isZeroNumber("E2"));
6331             ASSERT_EQUALS(false, Tokenizer::isZeroNumber("2e"));
6332         }
6333     
6334         void isOneNumber() const {
6335             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, Tokenizer::isOneNumber("1.0"));
6336             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, Tokenizer::isOneNumber("+1.0"));
6337             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, Tokenizer::isOneNumber("1.0e+0"));
6338             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, Tokenizer::isOneNumber("+1L"));
6339             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, Tokenizer::isOneNumber("+1"));
6340             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, Tokenizer::isOneNumber("1"));
6341             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, Tokenizer::isOneNumber("+1E+0"));
6342     
6343             ASSERT_EQUALS(false, Tokenizer::isOneNumber("0.0"));
6344             ASSERT_EQUALS(false, Tokenizer::isOneNumber("+0.0"));
6345             ASSERT_EQUALS(false, Tokenizer::isOneNumber("-0"));
6346             ASSERT_EQUALS(false, Tokenizer::isOneNumber(""));
6347             ASSERT_EQUALS(false, Tokenizer::isOneNumber("garbage"));
6348         }
6349

6352             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, Tokenizer::isTwoNumber("+2.0"));
6353             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, Tokenizer::isTwoNumber("2.0e+0"));
6354             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, Tokenizer::isTwoNumber("+2L"));
6355             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, Tokenizer::isTwoNumber("+2"));
6356             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, Tokenizer::isTwoNumber("2"));
6357             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, Tokenizer::isTwoNumber("+2E+0"));
6358     
6359             ASSERT_EQUALS(false, Tokenizer::isTwoNumber("0.0"));
6360             ASSERT_EQUALS(false, Tokenizer::isTwoNumber("+0.0"));
6361             ASSERT_EQUALS(false, Tokenizer::isTwoNumber("-0"));
6362             ASSERT_EQUALS(false, Tokenizer::isTwoNumber(""));
6363             ASSERT_EQUALS(false, Tokenizer::isTwoNumber("garbage"));
6364         }

6366         void simplifyMathFunctions_erfc() {
6367             // verify erfc(), erfcf(), erfcl() - simplifcation
6368             const char code_erfc[] ="void f(int x) {\n"
6369                                     " std::cout << erfc(x);\n" // do not simplify
6370                                     " std::cout << erfc(0L);\n" // simplify to 1
6371                                     "}";
6372             const char expected_erfc[] = "void f ( int x ) {\n"
6373                                          "std :: cout << erfc ( x ) ;\n"
6374                                          "std :: cout << 1 ;\n"
6375                                          "}";
6376             ASSERT_EQUALS(expected_erfc, tokenizeAndStringify(code_erfc));
6377     
6378             const char code_erfcf[] ="void f(float x) {\n"
6379                                      " std::cout << erfcf(x);\n" // do not simplify
6380                                      " std::cout << erfcf(0.0f);\n" // simplify to 1
6381                                      "}";
6382             const char expected_erfcf[] = "void f ( float x ) {\n"
6383                                           "std :: cout << erfcf ( x ) ;\n"
6384                                           "std :: cout << 1 ;\n"
6385                                           "}";
6386             ASSERT_EQUALS(expected_erfcf, tokenizeAndStringify(code_erfcf));
6387     
6388             const char code_erfcl[] ="void f(long double x) {\n"
6389                                      " std::cout << erfcl(x);\n" // do not simplify
6390                                      " std::cout << erfcl(0.0f);\n" // simplify to 1
6391                                      "}";
6392             const char expected_erfcl[] = "void f ( long double x ) {\n"
6393                                           "std :: cout << erfcl ( x ) ;\n"
6394                                           "std :: cout << 1 ;\n"
6395                                           "}";
6396             ASSERT_EQUALS(expected_erfcl, tokenizeAndStringify(code_erfcl));
6397         }

7376         void simplifyMathFunctions_div() {
7377             // verify div(), ldiv(), lldiv() - simplifcation
7378             const char code_div[] ="void f(int x) {\n"
7379                                    " std::cout << div(x,1);\n" //simplify
7380                                    " std::cout << div(x,-1);\n" // do not simplify
7381                                    " std::cout << ldiv(10L,1L);\n" // simplify
7382                                    " std::cout << ldiv(10L,132L);\n" // do not simplify
7383                                    " std::cout << lldiv(10LL,1LL);\n" // simplify
7384                                    " std::cout << lldiv(10LL,132LL);\n" // do not simplify
7385                                    "}";
7386     
7387             const char expected_div[] = "void f ( int x ) {\n"
7388                                         "std :: cout << x ;\n"
7389                                         "std :: cout << div ( x , -1 ) ;\n"
7390                                         "std :: cout << 10L ;\n"
7391                                         "std :: cout << ldiv ( 10L , 132L ) ;\n"
7392                                         "std :: cout << 10LL ;\n"
7393                                         "std :: cout << lldiv ( 10LL , 132LL ) ;\n"
7394                                         "}";
7395             ASSERT_EQUALS(expected_div, tokenizeAndStringify(code_div));
7396     
7397             // Do not simplify class members.
7398             // case: div
7399             const char code_div1[] = "int f(const Fred &fred) {return fred.div(12,3);}";
7400             const char expected_div1[] = "int f ( const Fred & fred ) { return fred . div ( 12 , 3 ) ; }";
7401             ASSERT_EQUALS(expected_div1, tokenizeAndStringify(code_div1));
7402             // case: ldiv
7403             const char code_div2[] = "int f(const Fred &fred) {return fred.ldiv(12,3);}";
7404             const char expected_div2[] = "int f ( const Fred & fred ) { return fred . ldiv ( 12 , 3 ) ; }";
7405             ASSERT_EQUALS(expected_div2, tokenizeAndStringify(code_div2));
7406             // case: lldiv
7407             const char code_div3[] = "int f(const Fred &fred) {return fred.lldiv(12,3);}";
7408             const char expected_div3[] = "int f ( const Fred & fred ) { return fred . lldiv ( 12 , 3 ) ; }";
7409             ASSERT_EQUALS(expected_div3, tokenizeAndStringify(code_div3));
7410         }

7412         void simplifyMathFunctions_pow() {
7413             // verify pow(),pow(),powl() - simplifcation
7414             const char code_pow[] ="void f() {\n"
7415                                    " std::cout << pow(-1.0,1);\n"
7416                                    " std::cout << pow(1.0,1);\n"
7417                                    " std::cout << pow(0,1);\n"
7418                                    " std::cout << pow(1,-6);\n"
7419                                    " std::cout << powf(-1.0,1.0f);\n"
7420                                    " std::cout << powf(1.0,1.0f);\n"
7421                                    " std::cout << powf(0,1.0f);\n"
7422                                    " std::cout << powf(1.0,-6.0f);\n"
7423                                    " std::cout << powl(-1.0,1.0);\n"
7424                                    " std::cout << powl(1.0,1.0);\n"
7425                                    " std::cout << powl(0,1.0);\n"
7426                                    " std::cout << powl(1.0,-6.0d);\n"
7427                                    "}";
7428     
7429             const char expected_pow[] = "void f ( ) {\n"
7430                                         "std :: cout << -1.0 ;\n"
7431                                         "std :: cout << 1 ;\n"
7432                                         "std :: cout << 0 ;\n"
7433                                         "std :: cout << 1 ;\n"
7434                                         "std :: cout << -1.0 ;\n"
7435                                         "std :: cout << 1 ;\n"
7436                                         "std :: cout << 0 ;\n"
7437                                         "std :: cout << 1 ;\n"
7438                                         "std :: cout << -1.0 ;\n"
7439                                         "std :: cout << 1 ;\n"
7440                                         "std :: cout << 0 ;\n"
7441                                         "std :: cout << 1 ;\n"
7442                                         "}";
7443             ASSERT_EQUALS(expected_pow, tokenizeAndStringify(code_pow));
7444     
7445             // verify if code is simplified correctly.
7446             // Do not simplify class members.
7447             const char code_pow1[] = "int f(const Fred &fred) {return fred.pow(12,3);}";
7448             const char expected_pow1[] = "int f ( const Fred & fred ) { return fred . pow ( 12 , 3 ) ; }";
7449             ASSERT_EQUALS(expected_pow1, tokenizeAndStringify(code_pow1));
7450     
7451             const char code_pow2[] = "int f() {return pow(0,0);}";
7452             const char expected_pow2[] = "int f ( ) { return 1 ; }";
7453             ASSERT_EQUALS(expected_pow2, tokenizeAndStringify(code_pow2));
7454     
7455             const char code_pow3[] = "int f() {return pow(0,1);}";
7456             const char expected_pow3[] = "int f ( ) { return 0 ; }";
7457             ASSERT_EQUALS(expected_pow3, tokenizeAndStringify(code_pow3));
7458

7460             const char expected_pow4[] = "int f ( ) { return 1 ; }";
7461             ASSERT_EQUALS(expected_pow4, tokenizeAndStringify(code_pow4));
7462         }

7470             ASSERT_EQUALS(expected_islessgreater, tokenizeAndStringify(code_islessgreater));

7473                                                "return islessgreater(0,1);\n" // (0 < 1) or (0 > 1) --> true
7474                                                "}";

7476             ASSERT_EQUALS(expected_islessgreater1, tokenizeAndStringify(code_islessgreater1));
7477     
7478             const char code_islessgreater2[] = "bool f(){\n"
7479                                                "return islessgreater(0,0);\n" // (0 < 0) or (0 > 0) --> false
7480                                                "}";

7482             ASSERT_EQUALS(expected_islessgreater2, tokenizeAndStringify(code_islessgreater2));

7488             ASSERT_EQUALS(expected_islessgreater3, tokenizeAndStringify(code_islessgreater3));

7665         void simplifyMathFunctions() { //#5031
7666             // verify abs,fabs,labs,llabs,atol simplifcation
7667             const char code1[] = "void foo() {\n"
7668                                  "    std::cout<<std::abs(0);\n"    // in std:: namespeace
7669                                  "    std::cout<<std::fabs(0.0);\n" // in std:: namespeace
7670                                  "    std::cout<<abs(0);\n"
7671                                  "    std::cout<<fabs(0.0);\n"
7672                                  "    std::cout<<labs(0);\n"
7673                                  "    std::cout<<llabs(0);\n"
7674                                  "    std::cout<<std::abs(-1);\n"    // in std:: namespeace
7675                                  "    std::cout<<std::fabs(-1.0);\n" // in std:: namespeace
7676                                  "    std::cout<<abs(-1);\n"
7677                                  "    std::cout<<fabs(-1.0);\n"
7678                                  "    std::cout<<labs(-1);\n"
7679                                  "    std::cout<<llabs(-1);\n"
7680                                  "    std::cout<<atol(\"1\");\n"
7681                                  "    std::cout<<atol(\"x\");\n"
7682                                  "    std::cout<<abs(atol(\"1\"));\n" // nested calls
7683                                  "}";
7684             const char expected1[] = "void foo ( ) {\n"
7685                                      "std :: cout << 0 ;\n"
7686                                      "std :: cout << 0.0 ;\n"
7687                                      "std :: cout << 0 ;\n"
7688                                      "std :: cout << 0.0 ;\n"
7689                                      "std :: cout << 0 ;\n"
7690                                      "std :: cout << 0 ;\n"
7691                                      "std :: cout << 1 ;\n"
7692                                      "std :: cout << 1.0 ;\n"
7693                                      "std :: cout << 1 ;\n"
7694                                      "std :: cout << 1.0 ;\n"
7695                                      "std :: cout << 1 ;\n"
7696                                      "std :: cout << 1 ;\n"
7697                                      "std :: cout << 1 ;\n"
7698                                      "std :: cout << atol ( \"x\" ) ;\n"
7699                                      "std :: cout << 1 ;\n"
7700                                      "}";
7701             ASSERT_EQUALS(expected1, tokenizeAndStringify(code1));
7702     
7703             // testcase from ticket #5031
7704             const char code2[]     = "extern int a; void f(){printf(\"%i\", abs(--a));}\n";
7705             const char expected2[] = "extern int a ; void f ( ) { printf ( \"%i\" , abs ( -- a ) ) ; }";
7706             ASSERT_EQUALS(expected2, tokenizeAndStringify(code2));
7707         }

7877         void simplifyStaticConst() {
7878             const char code1[]     = "class foo { public: bool const static c ; }";
7879             const char expected1[] = "class foo { public: static const bool c ; }";
7880             ASSERT_EQUALS(expected1, tokenizeAndStringify(code1, true));
7881     
7882             const char code2[] =
7883                 "int long long f()\n"

7895                 "int static const signed long long i11;\n"
7896                 "int static const long long signed i12;\n"
7897                 "long long signed int static const i13;\n"

7904                 "+ i13 + i14 + i15 + i16 + i17 + i18;\n"
7905                 "}";

7928                 "+ i13 + i14 + i15 + i16 + i17 + i18 ;\n"
7929                 "}";

7937         void simplifyDeprecated() {
7938             ASSERT_EQUALS("int f ( ) ;",
7939                           tokenizeAndStringify("[[deprecated]] int f();", false, true, Settings::Native, "test.cpp", true));
7940     
7941             ASSERT_EQUALS("[ [ deprecated ] ] int f ( ) ;",
7942                           tokenizeAndStringify("[[deprecated]] int f();", false, true, Settings::Native, "test.cpp", false));
7943     
7944             ASSERT_EQUALS("[ [ deprecated ] ] int f ( ) ;",
7945                           tokenizeAndStringify("[[deprecated]] int f();", false, true, Settings::Native, "test.c", true));
7946         }
7947     
7948         void simplifyCaseRange() {
7949             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { case 1 : case 2 : case 3 : case 4 : ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { case 1 ... 4: }"));
7950             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { case 4 . . . 1 : ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { case 4 ... 1: }"));
7951             tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { case 1 ... 1000000: }"); // Do not run out of memory
7952     
7953             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { case 'a' : case 'b' : case 'c' : ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { case 'a' ... 'c': }"));
7954             ASSERT_EQUALS("void f ( ) { case 'c' . . . 'a' : ; }", tokenizeAndStringify("void f() { case 'c' ... 'a': }"));
7955         }
7956     
7957         void prepareTernaryOpForAST() {
7958             ASSERT_EQUALS("a ? b : c ;", tokenizeAndStringify("a ? b : c;"));
7959     
7960             ASSERT_EQUALS("a ? ( b , c ) : d ;", tokenizeAndStringify("a ? b , c : d;"));
7961             ASSERT_EQUALS("a ? ( b , c ) : d ;", tokenizeAndStringify("a ? (b , c) : d;"));
7962     
7963             ASSERT_EQUALS("a ? ( 1 ? ( a , b ) : 3 ) : d ;", tokenizeAndStringify("a ? 1 ? a, b : 3 : d;"));
7964         }
7965     
7966         std::string testAst(const char code[],bool verbose=false) {
7967             // tokenize given code..
7968             Tokenizer tokenList(&settings0, nullptr);
7969             std::istringstream istr(code);
7970             if (!tokenList.list.createTokens(istr,"test.cpp"))
7971                 return "ERROR";
7972     
7973             tokenList.combineOperators();
7974             tokenList.createLinks();
7975             tokenList.createLinks2();
7976     
7977             // Create AST..
7978             tokenList.prepareTernaryOpForAST();
7979             tokenList.list.createAst();
7980     
7981             // Basic AST validation
7982             for (const Token *tok = tokenList.list.front(); tok; tok = tok->next()) {
7983                 if (tok->astOperand2() && !tok->astOperand1() && tok->str() != ";" && tok->str() != ":")
7984                     return "Op2 but no Op1 for token: " + tok->str();
7985             }
7986     
7987             // Return stringified AST
7988             if (verbose)
7989                 return tokenList.list.front()->astTop()->astStringVerbose(0, 0);
7990     
7991             std::string ret;
7992             std::set<const Token *> astTop;
7993             for (const Token *tok = tokenList.list.front(); tok; tok = tok->next()) {
7994                 if (tok->astOperand1() && astTop.find(tok->astTop()) == astTop.end()) {
7995                     astTop.insert(tok->astTop());
7996                     if (!ret.empty())
7997                         ret = ret + " ";
7998                     ret += tok->astTop()->astString();
7999                 }
8000             }
8001             return ret;
8002         }

8004         void astexpr() { // simple expressions with arithmetical ops
8005             ASSERT_EQUALS("12+3+", testAst("1+2+3"));
8006             ASSERT_EQUALS("12*3+", testAst("1*2+3"));
8007             ASSERT_EQUALS("123*+", testAst("1+2*3"));
8008             ASSERT_EQUALS("12*34*+", testAst("1*2+3*4"));
8009             ASSERT_EQUALS("12*34*5*+", testAst("1*2+3*4*5"));
8010             ASSERT_EQUALS("0(r.&", testAst("(&((typeof(x))0).r);"));
8011             ASSERT_EQUALS("0(r.&", testAst("&((typeof(x))0).r;"));
8012     
8013             // Various tests of precedence
8014             ASSERT_EQUALS("ab::c+", testAst("a::b+c"));
8015             ASSERT_EQUALS("abc+=", testAst("a=b+c"));
8016             ASSERT_EQUALS("abc=,", testAst("a,b=c"));
8017             ASSERT_EQUALS("a-1+", testAst("-a+1"));
8018             ASSERT_EQUALS("ab++-c-", testAst("a-b++-c"));
8019     
8020             // sizeof
8021             ASSERT_EQUALS("ab.sizeof", testAst("sizeof a.b"));
8022     
8023             // assignment operators
8024             ASSERT_EQUALS("ab>>=", testAst("a>>=b;"));
8025             ASSERT_EQUALS("ab<<=", testAst("a<<=b;"));
8026             ASSERT_EQUALS("ab+=",  testAst("a+=b;"));
8027             ASSERT_EQUALS("ab-=",  testAst("a-=b;"));
8028             ASSERT_EQUALS("ab*=",  testAst("a*=b;"));
8029             ASSERT_EQUALS("ab/=",  testAst("a/=b;"));
8030             ASSERT_EQUALS("ab%=",  testAst("a%=b;"));
8031             ASSERT_EQUALS("ab&=",  testAst("a&=b;"));
8032             ASSERT_EQUALS("ab|=",  testAst("a|=b;"));
8033             ASSERT_EQUALS("ab^=",  testAst("a^=b;"));
8034     
8035             ASSERT_EQUALS("ab*c*.(+return", testAst("return a + ((*b).*c)();"));
8036     
8037             // assignments are executed from right to left
8038             ASSERT_EQUALS("abc==", testAst("a=b=c;"));
8039     
8040             // ternary operator
8041             ASSERT_EQUALS("ab0=c1=:?", testAst("a?b=0:c=1;"));
8042             ASSERT_EQUALS("fabc,d:?=e,", testAst("f = a ? b, c : d, e;"));
8043             ASSERT_EQUALS("fabc,de,:?=", testAst("f = (a ? (b, c) : (d, e));"));
8044             ASSERT_EQUALS("fabc,de,:?=", testAst("f = (a ? b, c : (d, e));"));
8045             ASSERT_EQUALS("ab35,4:?foo(:?return", testAst("return (a ? b ? (3,5) : 4 : foo());"));
8046             ASSERT_EQUALS("check(result_type00,{invalid:?return", testAst("return check() ? result_type {0, 0} : invalid;"));
8047     
8048             ASSERT_EQUALS("a\"\"=", testAst("a=\"\""));
8049             ASSERT_EQUALS("a\'\'=", testAst("a=\'\'"));
8050             ASSERT_EQUALS("a1[\"\"=", testAst("char a[1]=\"\";"));
8051     
8052             ASSERT_EQUALS("'X''a'>", testAst("('X' > 'a')"));
8053             ASSERT_EQUALS("'X''a'>", testAst("(L'X' > L'a')"));
8054     
8055             ASSERT_EQUALS("a0>bc/d:?", testAst("(a>0) ? (b/(c)) : d;"));
8056             ASSERT_EQUALS("abc/+d+", testAst("a + (b/(c)) + d;"));
8057             ASSERT_EQUALS("f( x1024x/0:?", testAst("void f() { x ? 1024 / x : 0; }"));
8058     
8059             ASSERT_EQUALS("absizeofd(ef.+(=", testAst("a = b(sizeof(c d) + e.f)"));
8060     
8061             ASSERT_EQUALS("a*b***", testAst("*a * **b;")); // Correctly distinguish between unary and binary operator*
8062     
8063             // strings
8064             ASSERT_EQUALS("f\"A\"1,(",testAst("f(\"A\" B, 1);"));
8065             ASSERT_EQUALS("fA1,(",testAst("f(A \"B\", 1);"));
8066     
8067             // for
8068             ASSERT_EQUALS("for;;(", testAst("for(;;)"));
8069             ASSERT_EQUALS("fora0=a8<a++;;(", testAst("for(a=0;a<8;a++)"));
8070             ASSERT_EQUALS("fori1=current0=,iNUM<=i++;;(", testAst("for(i = (1), current = 0; i <= (NUM); ++i)"));
8071             ASSERT_EQUALS("foreachxy,((", testAst("for(each(x,y)){}"));  // it's not well-defined what this ast should be
8072             ASSERT_EQUALS("forab:(", testAst("for (int a : b);"));
8073             ASSERT_EQUALS("forx*0=yz;;(", testAst("for(*x=0;y;z)"));
8074     
8075             // problems with multiple expressions
8076             ASSERT_EQUALS("ax( whilex(", testAst("a(x) while (x)"));
8077             ASSERT_EQUALS("ifx( i0= whilei(", testAst("if (x) { ({ int i = 0; while(i); }) };"));
8078             ASSERT_EQUALS("ifx( BUG_ON{!( i0= whilei(", testAst("if (x) { BUG_ON(!({int i=0; while(i);})); }"));
8079             ASSERT_EQUALS("v0= while{0!=( v0= while{0!=( v0=", testAst("({ v = 0; }); while (({ v = 0; }) != 0); while (({ v = 0; }) != 0);"));
8080     
8081     
8082             ASSERT_EQUALS("abc.1:?1+bd.1:?+=", testAst("a =(b.c ? : 1) + 1 + (b.d ? : 1);"));
8083     
8084             ASSERT_EQUALS("try{ catch.(", testAst("try {} catch (...) {}"));
8085     
8086             ASSERT_EQUALS("FooBar(", testAst("void Foo(Bar&);"));
8087             ASSERT_EQUALS("FooBar(", testAst("void Foo(Bar& &);")); // Rvalue reference - simplified from && to & & by real tokenizer
8088             ASSERT_EQUALS("DerivedDerived::(", testAst("Derived::~Derived() {}"));
8089     
8090             ASSERT_EQUALS("ifCA_FarReadfilenew(,sizeofobjtype(,(!(", testAst("if (!CA_FarRead(file, (void far *)new, sizeof(objtype)))")); // #5910 - don't hang if C code is parsed as C++
8091         }

8093         void astnewdelete() {
8094             ASSERT_EQUALS("aintnew=", testAst("a = new int;"));
8095             ASSERT_EQUALS("aint4[new=", testAst("a = new int[4];"));
8096             ASSERT_EQUALS("aFoobar(new=", testAst("a = new Foo(bar);"));
8097             ASSERT_EQUALS("aFoobar(new=", testAst("a = new Foo(bar);"));
8098             ASSERT_EQUALS("aFoo(new=", testAst("a = new Foo<bar>();"));
8099             ASSERT_EQUALS("X12,3,(new", testAst("new (a,b,c) X(1,2,3);"));
8100             ASSERT_EQUALS("aXnew(", testAst("a (new (X));"));
8101             ASSERT_EQUALS("aXnew5,(", testAst("a (new (X), 5);"));

8103             ASSERT_EQUALS("adelete", testAst("delete (a);"));
8104             ASSERT_EQUALS("adelete", testAst("delete[] a;"));
8105             ASSERT_EQUALS("ab.3c-(delete", testAst("delete[] a.b(3 - c);"));
8106             ASSERT_EQUALS("a::new=", testAst("a = new (b) ::X;"));
8107             ASSERT_EQUALS("aA1(new(bB2(new(,", testAst("a(new A(1)), b(new B(2))"));
8108             ASSERT_EQUALS("Fred10[new", testAst(";new Fred[10];"));
8109             ASSERT_EQUALS("f( adelete", testAst("void f() { delete a; }"));
8110     
8111             // invalid code (libreoffice), don't hang

8113             // SfxViewFrame* pFrame;
8114             // new SlideSorterViewShell(pFrame,rViewShellBase,pParentWindow,pFrameViewArgument);
8115             ASSERT_EQUALS("fxnewy,z,(", testAst("f(new (x,y,z));"));
8116

8119             ASSERT_EQUALS("autonew", testAst("new (auto) (0.0);"));
8120             ASSERT_EQUALS("int3[4[5[new", testAst("new (int S::*[3][4][5]) ();"));
8121             ASSERT_EQUALS("pSnew=", testAst("p=new (x)(S)(1,2);"));
8122             ASSERT_EQUALS("inti[new(", testAst("(void)new (int[i]);"));
8123             ASSERT_EQUALS("intp* pnew malloc4(", testAst("int*p; new (p) (malloc(4));"));
8124             ASSERT_EQUALS("intnew", testAst("new (&w.x)(int*)(0);"));
8125             ASSERT_EQUALS("&new", testAst("new (&w.x)(0);")); // <- the "(int*)" has been simplified
8126     
8127             // gcc testsuite..
8128             ASSERT_EQUALS("char10[new(", testAst("(void)new(char*)[10];"));
8129         }

8131         void astpar() { // parentheses
8132             ASSERT_EQUALS("12+3*", testAst("(1+2)*3"));
8133             ASSERT_EQUALS("123+*", testAst("1*(2+3)"));
8134             ASSERT_EQUALS("123+*4*", testAst("1*(2+3)*4"));
8135             ASSERT_EQUALS("ifab.c&d==(", testAst("if((a.b&c)==d){}"));
8136     
8137             ASSERT_EQUALS("pf.pf.12,(&&", testAst("((p.f) && (p.f)(1,2))"));
8138     
8139             // problems with: if (x[y]==z)
8140             ASSERT_EQUALS("ifa(0[1==(", testAst("if(a()[0]==1){}"));
8141             ASSERT_EQUALS("ifbuff0[&(*1==(", testAst("if (*((DWORD*)&buff[0])==1){}"));
8142             ASSERT_EQUALS("ifp*0[1==(", testAst("if((*p)[0]==1)"));
8143             ASSERT_EQUALS("ifab.cd.[e==(", testAst("if(a.b[c.d]==e){}"));
8144

8146             ASSERT_EQUALS("ab.i[j1+[", testAst("a.b[i][j+1]"));
8147

8149             ASSERT_EQUALS("=\n"
8150                           "|-x\n"
8151                           "`-(\n"
8152                           "  `-.\n"
8153                           "    |-[\n"
8154                           "    | |-a\n"
8155                           "    | `-i\n"
8156                           "    `-f\n",
8157                           testAst("x = ((a[i]).f)();", true));
8158             ASSERT_EQUALS("abc.de.++[=", testAst("a = b.c[++(d.e)];"));
8159             ASSERT_EQUALS("abc(1+=", testAst("a = b(c**)+1;"));

8161

8163             ASSERT_EQUALS("a1(2(+=",testAst("a=(t)1+(t)2;"));
8164             ASSERT_EQUALS("a1(2+=",testAst("a=(t)1+2;"));
8165             ASSERT_EQUALS("a1(2+=",testAst("a=(t*)1+2;"));
8166             ASSERT_EQUALS("a1(2+=",testAst("a=(t&)1+2;"));
8167             ASSERT_EQUALS("ab::r&c(=", testAst("a::b& r = (a::b&)c;")); // #5261
8168             ASSERT_EQUALS("ab10:?=", testAst("a=(b)?1:0;"));
8169

8173             ASSERT_EQUALS("xa{((= bc( yd{((= ef(",
8174                           testAst("x=(int)(a({b(c);}));" // don't hang
8175                                   "y=(int)(d({e(f);}));"));
8176             ASSERT_EQUALS("QT_WA{{,( QT_WA{{,( x1=",
8177                           testAst("QT_WA({},{x=0;});" // don't hang
8178                                   "QT_WA({x=1;},{x=2;});"));
8179             ASSERT_EQUALS("xMACROtypeT=value1=,{({=",
8180                           testAst("x = { MACRO( { .type=T, .value=1 } ) }")); // dont hang: MACRO({..})

8182     
8183             // function pointer
8184             TODO_ASSERT_EQUALS("todo", "va_argapvoid((,(*0=", testAst("*va_arg(ap, void(**) ()) = 0;"));
8185     
8186             // struct initialization
8187             ASSERT_EQUALS("name_bytes[bits~unusedBits>>unusedBits<<{=", testAst("const uint8_t name_bytes[] = { (~bits >> unusedBits) << unusedBits };"));
8188             ASSERT_EQUALS("abuf0{={=", testAst("a = { .buf = { 0 } };"));
8189             ASSERT_EQUALS("tset{=", testAst("struct cgroup_taskset tset = {};"));
8190             ASSERT_EQUALS("s1a&,{2b&,{,{=", testAst("s = { {1, &a}, {2, &b} };"));
8191     
8192             // template parentheses: <>
8193             ASSERT_EQUALS("stdfabs::m_similarity(numeric_limitsepsilon::(<=return", testAst("return std::fabs(m_similarity) <= numeric_limits<double>::epsilon();")); // #6195
8194

8196             ASSERT_EQUALS("Class{", testAst("Class{};"));
8197             ASSERT_EQUALS("Class12,{", testAst("Class{1,2};"));
8198             ASSERT_EQUALS("Class12,{", testAst("Class<X>{1,2};"));
8199             ASSERT_EQUALS("abc{d:?=", testAst("a=b?c{}:d;"));
8200             ASSERT_EQUALS("abc12,{d:?=", testAst("a=b?c{1,2}:d;"));
8201             ASSERT_EQUALS("abc{d:?=", testAst("a=b?c<X>{}:d;"));
8202             ASSERT_EQUALS("abc12,{d:?=", testAst("a=b?c<X>{1,2}:d;"));
8203             ASSERT_EQUALS("a::12,{", testAst("::a{1,2};")); // operator precedence
8204             ASSERT_EQUALS("Abc({newreturn", testAst("return new A {b(c)};"));
8205         }

8229             ASSERT_EQUALS("ab4<<c--+1:?", testAst("a ? (b << 4) + --c : 1"));
8230             ASSERT_EQUALS("ab4<<c--+1:?", testAst("a ? (b << 4) + c-- : 1"));
8231             ASSERT_EQUALS("ai[i= i--", testAst("a[i]=i; --i;"));
8232         }

8259         void astcast() {
8260             ASSERT_EQUALS("ac&(=", testAst("a = (long)&c;"));
8261             ASSERT_EQUALS("ac*(=", testAst("a = (Foo*)*c;"));
8262             ASSERT_EQUALS("ac-(=", testAst("a = (long)-c;"));
8263             ASSERT_EQUALS("ac~(=", testAst("a = (b)~c;"));
8264             ASSERT_EQUALS("ac(=", testAst("a = (some<strange, type>)c;"));
8265             ASSERT_EQUALS("afoveon_avgimage((foveon_avgimage((+=", testAst("a = foveon_avg(((short(*)[4]) image)) + foveon_avg(((short(*)[4]) image));"));
8266             ASSERT_EQUALS("c(40<<return", testAst("return (long long)c << 40;"));
8267             ASSERT_EQUALS("ab-(=", testAst("a = ((int)-b)")); // Multiple subsequent unary operators (cast and -)
8268             ASSERT_EQUALS("xdouble123(i*(=", testAst("x = (int)(double(123)*i);"));
8269     
8270             // not cast
8271             ASSERT_EQUALS("AB||", testAst("(A)||(B)"));
8272         }
8273     
8274         void astlambda() {
8275             // a lambda expression '[x](y){}' is compiled as:
8276             // [
8277             // `-(
8278             //   `-{
8279             ASSERT_EQUALS("x{([( ai=", testAst("x([&a](int i){a=i;});"));
8280     
8281             ASSERT_EQUALS("{([(return 0return", testAst("return [](){ return 0; }();"));
8282             ASSERT_EQUALS("{([(return 0return", testAst("return []() -> int { return 0; }();"));
8283             ASSERT_EQUALS("{([(return 0return", testAst("return [something]() -> int { return 0; }();"));
8284             ASSERT_EQUALS("{([cd,(return 0return", testAst("return [](int a, int b) -> int { return 0; }(c, d);"));
8285     
8286             ASSERT_EQUALS("x{([= 0return", testAst("x = [](){return 0; };"));
8287         }
8288     
8289         void compileLimits() {
8290             const char raw_code[] = "#define PTR1 (* (* (* (* (* (* (* (* (* (*\n"
8291                                     "#define PTR2 PTR1 PTR1 PTR1 PTR1 PTR1 PTR1 PTR1 PTR1 PTR1 PTR1\n"
8292                                     "#define PTR3 PTR2 PTR2 PTR2 PTR2 PTR2 PTR2 PTR2 PTR2 PTR2 PTR2\n"
8293                                     "#define PTR4 PTR3 PTR3 PTR3 PTR3 PTR3 PTR3 PTR3 PTR3 PTR3 PTR3\n"
8294                                     "#define PTR5 PTR4 PTR4 PTR4 PTR4 PTR4 PTR4 PTR4 PTR4 PTR4 PTR4\n"
8295                                     "#define PTR6 PTR5 PTR5 PTR5 PTR5 PTR5 PTR5 PTR5 PTR5 PTR5 PTR5\n"
8296                                     "\n"
8297                                     "#define RBR1 ) ) ) ) ) ) ) ) ) )\n"
8298                                     "#define RBR2 RBR1 RBR1 RBR1 RBR1 RBR1 RBR1 RBR1 RBR1 RBR1 RBR1\n"
8299                                     "#define RBR3 RBR2 RBR2 RBR2 RBR2 RBR2 RBR2 RBR2 RBR2 RBR2 RBR2\n"
8300                                     "#define RBR4 RBR3 RBR3 RBR3 RBR3 RBR3 RBR3 RBR3 RBR3 RBR3 RBR3\n"
8301                                     "#define RBR5 RBR4 RBR4 RBR4 RBR4 RBR4 RBR4 RBR4 RBR4 RBR4 RBR4\n"
8302                                     "#define RBR6 RBR5 RBR5 RBR5 RBR5 RBR5 RBR5 RBR5 RBR5 RBR5 RBR5\n"
8303                                     "\n"
8304                                     "int PTR4 q4_var RBR4 = 0;\n";
8305     
8306             // Preprocess file..
8307             Preprocessor preprocessor(settings0);
8308             std::list<std::string> configurations;
8309             std::string filedata = "";
8310             std::istringstream fin(raw_code);
8311             preprocessor.preprocess(fin, filedata, configurations, emptyString, settings0.includePaths);
8312             const std::string code = preprocessor.getcode(filedata, emptyString, emptyString);
8313     
8314             tokenizeAndStringify(code.c_str()); // just survive...
8315         }
8316     
8317         bool isStartOfExecutableScope(int offset, const char code[]) {
8318             Tokenizer tokenizer(&settings0, this);
8319             std::istringstream istr(code);
8320             tokenizer.tokenize(istr, "test.cpp");
8321     
8322             return Tokenizer::startOfExecutableScope(tokenizer.tokens()->tokAt(offset)) != nullptr;
8323         }
8324     
8325         void startOfExecutableScope() {
8326             ASSERT(isStartOfExecutableScope(3, "void foo() { }"));
8327             ASSERT(isStartOfExecutableScope(3, "void foo() const { }"));
8328             ASSERT(isStartOfExecutableScope(3, "void foo() volatile { }"));
8329             ASSERT(isStartOfExecutableScope(3, "void foo() override { }"));
8330             ASSERT(isStartOfExecutableScope(3, "void foo() noexcept { }"));
8331             ASSERT(isStartOfExecutableScope(3, "void foo() NOEXCEPT { }"));
8332             ASSERT(isStartOfExecutableScope(3, "void foo() CONST NOEXCEPT { }"));
8333             ASSERT(isStartOfExecutableScope(3, "void foo() const noexcept { }"));
8334             ASSERT(isStartOfExecutableScope(3, "void foo() noexcept(true) { }"));
8335             ASSERT(isStartOfExecutableScope(3, "void foo() const noexcept(true) { }"));
8336             ASSERT(isStartOfExecutableScope(3, "void foo() throw() { }"));
8337             ASSERT(isStartOfExecutableScope(3, "void foo() THROW() { }"));
8338             ASSERT(isStartOfExecutableScope(3, "void foo() CONST THROW() { }"));
8339             ASSERT(isStartOfExecutableScope(3, "void foo() const throw() { }"));
8340             ASSERT(isStartOfExecutableScope(3, "void foo() throw(int) { }"));
8341             ASSERT(isStartOfExecutableScope(3, "void foo() const throw(int) { }"));
8342             ASSERT(isStartOfExecutableScope(2, "foo() : a(1) { }"));
8343             ASSERT(isStartOfExecutableScope(2, "foo() : a(1), b(2) { }"));
8344             ASSERT(isStartOfExecutableScope(2, "foo() : a{1} { }"));
8345             ASSERT(isStartOfExecutableScope(2, "foo() : a{1}, b{2} { }"));
8346         }
8347     
8348         void removeMacroInClassDef() { // #6058
8349             ASSERT_EQUALS("class Fred { } ;", tokenizeAndStringify("class DLLEXPORT Fred { } ;"));
8350             ASSERT_EQUALS("class Fred : Base { } ;", tokenizeAndStringify("class Fred FINAL : Base { } ;"));
8351             // Regression for C code:
8352             ASSERT_EQUALS("struct Fred { } ;", tokenizeAndStringify("struct DLLEXPORT Fred { } ;", false, true, Settings::Native, "test.c"));
8353         }
8354     
8355         void sizeofAddParentheses() {
8356             ASSERT_EQUALS("sizeof ( sizeof ( 1 ) ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("sizeof sizeof 1;"));
8357             ASSERT_EQUALS("sizeof ( a . b ) + 3 ;", tokenizeAndStringify("sizeof a.b+3;"));
8358             ASSERT_EQUALS("sizeof ( a [ 2 ] . b ) + 3 ;", tokenizeAndStringify("sizeof a[2].b+3;"));
8359             ASSERT_EQUALS("f ( 0 , sizeof ( ptr . bar ) ) ;", tokenizeAndStringify("f(0, sizeof ptr->bar );"));
8360         }
